64JSNativeContextSpecialization::JSNativeContextSpecialization(
65 Editor* editor, JSGraph* jsgraph, JSHeapBroker* broker, Flags flags,
66 Zone* zone, Zone* shared_zone)
67 : AdvancedReducer(editor),

69 broker_(broker),
70 flags_(flags),
71 global_object_(
72 broker->target_native_context().global_object(broker).object()),

80Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::Reduce(Node* node) {
81 switch (node->opcode()) {
82 case IrOpcode::kJSAdd:
83 return ReduceJSAdd(node);
84 case IrOpcode::kJSAsyncFunctionEnter:
85 return ReduceJSAsyncFunctionEnter(node);
86 case IrOpcode::kJSAsyncFunctionReject:
87 return ReduceJSAsyncFunctionReject(node);
88 case IrOpcode::kJSAsyncFunctionResolve:
89 return ReduceJSAsyncFunctionResolve(node);
90 case IrOpcode::kJSGetSuperConstructor:
91 return ReduceJSGetSuperConstructor(node);
92 case IrOpcode::kJSFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct:
93 return ReduceJSFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct(node);
94 case IrOpcode::kJSInstanceOf:
95 return ReduceJSInstanceOf(node);
96 case IrOpcode::kJSHasInPrototypeChain:
97 return ReduceJSHasInPrototypeChain(node);
98 case IrOpcode::kJSOrdinaryHasInstance:
99 return ReduceJSOrdinaryHasInstance(node);
100 case IrOpcode::kJSPromiseResolve:
101 return ReduceJSPromiseResolve(node);
102 case IrOpcode::kJSResolvePromise:
103 return ReduceJSResolvePromise(node);
104 case IrOpcode::kJSLoadGlobal:
105 return ReduceJSLoadGlobal(node);
106 case IrOpcode::kJSStoreGlobal:
107 return ReduceJSStoreGlobal(node);
108 case IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamed:
109 return ReduceJSLoadNamed(node);
110 case IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamedFromSuper:
111 return ReduceJSLoadNamedFromSuper(node);
112 case IrOpcode::kJSSetNamedProperty:
113 return ReduceJSSetNamedProperty(node);
114 case IrOpcode::kJSHasProperty:
115 return ReduceJSHasProperty(node);
116 case IrOpcode::kJSLoadProperty:
117 return ReduceJSLoadProperty(node);
118 case IrOpcode::kJSSetKeyedProperty:
119 return ReduceJSSetKeyedProperty(node);
120 case IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnProperty:
121 return ReduceJSDefineKeyedOwnProperty(node);
122 case IrOpcode::kJSDefineNamedOwnProperty:
123 return ReduceJSDefineNamedOwnProperty(node);
124 case IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral:
125 return ReduceJSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral(node);
126 case IrOpcode::kJSStoreInArrayLiteral:
127 return ReduceJSStoreInArrayLiteral(node);
128 case IrOpcode::kJSToObject:
129 return ReduceJSToObject(node);
130 case IrOpcode::kJSToString:
131 return ReduceJSToString(node);
132 case IrOpcode::kJSGetIterator:
133 return ReduceJSGetIterator(node);
134 default:
135 break;
136 }
137 return NoChange();
138}

140// If {node} is a HeapConstant<String>, return the String's length. If {node} is
141// a number, return the maximum size that a stringified number can have.
142// Otherwise, we can't easily convert {node} into a String, and we return
143// nullopt.
144// static
145std::optional<size_t> JSNativeContextSpecialization::GetMaxStringLength(
146 JSHeapBroker* broker, Node* node) {
147 HeapObjectMatcher matcher(node);
148 if (matcher.HasResolvedValue() && matcher.Ref(broker).IsString()) {
149 StringRef input = matcher.Ref(broker).AsString();
150 return input.length();
151 }
152
153 NumberMatcher number_matcher(node);
154 if (number_matcher.HasResolvedValue()) {
155 return kMaxDoubleStringLength;
156 }
157
158 // We don't support objects with possibly monkey-patched prototype.toString
159 // as it might have side-effects, so we shouldn't attempt lowering them.
160 return std::nullopt;
161}

163Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSToString(Node* node) {
164 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSToString, node->opcode());
165 Node* const input = node->InputAt(0);
166
167 HeapObjectMatcher matcher(input);
168 if (matcher.HasResolvedValue() && matcher.Ref(broker()).IsString()) {
169 Reduction reduction = Changed(input); // JSToString(x:string) => x
170 ReplaceWithValue(node, reduction.replacement());
171 return reduction;
172 }
173
174 // TODO(turbofan): This optimization is weaker than what we used to have
175 // in js-typed-lowering for OrderedNumbers. We don't have types here though,
176 // so alternative approach should be designed if this causes performance
177 // regressions and the stronger optimization should be re-implemented.
178 NumberMatcher number_matcher(input);
179 if (number_matcher.HasResolvedValue()) {
180 DirectHandle<Object> num_obj =
181 broker()
182 ->local_isolate_or_isolate()
183 ->factory()
184 ->NewNumber<AllocationType::kOld>(number_matcher.ResolvedValue());
185 Handle<String> num_str =
186 broker()->local_isolate_or_isolate()->factory()->NumberToString(
187 num_obj);
188 Node* reduced = graph()->NewNode(
189 common()->HeapConstant(broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(num_str)));
190
191 ReplaceWithValue(node, reduced);
192 return Replace(reduced);
193 }
194
195 return NoChange();
196}

198// Return a String from {node}, which should be either a HeapConstant<String>
199// (in which case we return the String), or a number (in which case we convert
200// it to a String).
201Handle<String> JSNativeContextSpecialization::CreateStringConstant(Node* node) {
202 DCHECK(IrOpcode::IsConstantOpcode(node->opcode()));
203 NumberMatcher number_matcher(node);
204 if (number_matcher.HasResolvedValue()) {
205 DirectHandle<Object> num_obj =
206 broker()
207 ->local_isolate_or_isolate()
208 ->factory()
209 ->NewNumber<AllocationType::kOld>(number_matcher.ResolvedValue());
210 // Note that we do not store the result of NumberToString in
211 // {created_strings_}, because the latter is used to know if strings are
212 // safe to be used in the background, but we always have as additional
213 // information the node from which the string was created ({node} is that
214 // case), and if this node is a kHeapNumber, then we know that we must have
215 // created the string, and that there it is safe to read. So, we don't need
216 // {created_strings_} in that case.
217 return broker()->local_isolate_or_isolate()->factory()->NumberToString(
218 num_obj);
219 } else {
220 HeapObjectMatcher matcher(node);
221 if (matcher.HasResolvedValue() && matcher.Ref(broker()).IsString()) {
222 return matcher.Ref(broker()).AsString().object();
223 } else {
224 UNREACHABLE();
225 }
226 }
227}

230bool IsStringConstant(JSHeapBroker* broker, Node* node) {
231 HeapObjectMatcher matcher(node);
232 return matcher.HasResolvedValue() && matcher.Ref(broker).IsString();
233}

235bool IsStringWithNonAccessibleContent(JSHeapBroker* broker, Node* node) {
236 HeapObjectMatcher matcher(node);
237 if (matcher.HasResolvedValue() && matcher.Ref(broker).IsString()) {
238 StringRef input = matcher.Ref(broker).AsString();
239 return !input.IsContentAccessible();
240 }
241 return false;
242}

245Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSAsyncFunctionEnter(
246 Node* node) {
247 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSAsyncFunctionEnter, node->opcode());
248 Node* closure = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
249 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
250 Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
251 Node* frame_state = NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node);
252 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
253 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
254
255 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) return NoChange();
256
257 // Create the promise for the async function.
258 Node* promise = effect =
259 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreatePromise(), context, effect);
260
261 // Create the JSAsyncFunctionObject based on the SharedFunctionInfo
262 // extracted from the top-most frame in {frame_state}.
263 SharedFunctionInfoRef shared = MakeRef(
264 broker(),
265 FrameStateInfoOf(frame_state->op()).shared_info().ToHandleChecked());
266 DCHECK(shared.is_compiled());
267 int register_count =
268 shared.internal_formal_parameter_count_without_receiver() +
269 shared.GetBytecodeArray(broker()).register_count();
270 MapRef fixed_array_map = broker()->fixed_array_map();
271 AllocationBuilder ab(jsgraph(), broker(), effect, control);
272 if (!ab.CanAllocateArray(register_count, fixed_array_map)) {
273 return NoChange();
274 }
275 Node* value = effect =
276 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreateAsyncFunctionObject(register_count),
277 closure, receiver, promise, context, effect, control);
278 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
279 return Replace(value);
280}

282Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSAsyncFunctionReject(
283 Node* node) {
284 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSAsyncFunctionReject, node->opcode());
285 Node* async_function_object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
286 Node* reason = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
287 Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
288 Node* frame_state = NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node);
289 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
290 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
291
292 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) return NoChange();
293
294 // Load the promise from the {async_function_object}.
295 Node* promise = effect = graph()->NewNode(
296 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSAsyncFunctionObjectPromise()),
297 async_function_object, effect, control);
298
299 // Create a nested frame state inside the current method's most-recent
300 // {frame_state} that will ensure that lazy deoptimizations at this
301 // point will still return the {promise} instead of the result of the
302 // JSRejectPromise operation (which yields undefined).
303 Node* parameters[] = {promise};
304 frame_state = CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
305 jsgraph(), Builtin::kAsyncFunctionLazyDeoptContinuation, context,
306 parameters, arraysize(parameters), frame_state,
307 ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
308
309 // Disable the additional debug event for the rejection since a
310 // debug event already happend for the exception that got us here.
311 Node* debug_event = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
312 effect = graph()->NewNode(javascript()->RejectPromise(), promise, reason,
313 debug_event, context, frame_state, effect, control);
314 ReplaceWithValue(node, promise, effect, control);
315 return Replace(promise);
316}

318Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSAsyncFunctionResolve(
319 Node* node) {
320 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSAsyncFunctionResolve, node->opcode());
321 Node* async_function_object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
322 Node* value = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
323 Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
324 Node* frame_state = NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node);
325 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
326 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
327
328 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) return NoChange();
329
330 // Load the promise from the {async_function_object}.
331 Node* promise = effect = graph()->NewNode(
332 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSAsyncFunctionObjectPromise()),
333 async_function_object, effect, control);
334
335 // Create a nested frame state inside the current method's most-recent
336 // {frame_state} that will ensure that lazy deoptimizations at this
337 // point will still return the {promise} instead of the result of the
338 // JSResolvePromise operation (which yields undefined).
339 Node* parameters[] = {promise};
340 frame_state = CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
341 jsgraph(), Builtin::kAsyncFunctionLazyDeoptContinuation, context,
342 parameters, arraysize(parameters), frame_state,
343 ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
344
345 effect = graph()->NewNode(javascript()->ResolvePromise(), promise, value,
346 context, frame_state, effect, control);
347 ReplaceWithValue(node, promise, effect, control);
348 return Replace(promise);
349}

351// Concatenates {left} and {right}. The result is fairly similar to creating a
352// new ConsString with {left} and {right} and then flattening it, which we don't
353// do because String::Flatten does not support background threads. Rather than
354// implementing a full String::Flatten for background threads, we prefered to
355// implement this Concatenate function, which, unlike String::Flatten, doesn't
356// need to replace ConsStrings by ThinStrings.
357Handle<String> JSNativeContextSpecialization::Concatenate(
358 Handle<String> left, Handle<String> right) {
359 if (left->length() == 0) return right;
360 if (right->length() == 0) return left;
361
362 // Repeated concatenations have a quadratic cost (eg, "s+=a;s+=b;s+=c;...").
363 // Rather than doing static analysis to determine how many concatenations we
364 // there are and how many uses the result of each concatenation have, we
365 // generate ConsString when the result of the concatenation would have more
366 // than {kConstantStringFlattenMaxSize} characters, and flattened SeqString
367 // otherwise.
368 // TODO(dmercadier): ideally, we would like to get rid of this constant, and
369 // always flatten. This requires some care to avoid the quadratic worst-case.
370 constexpr int32_t kConstantStringFlattenMaxSize = 100;
371
372 int32_t length = left->length() + right->length();
373 if (length > kConstantStringFlattenMaxSize) {
374 // The generational write-barrier doesn't work in background threads, so,
375 // if {left} or {right} are in the young generation, we would have to copy
376 // them to the local heap (which is old) before creating the (old)
377 // ConsString. But, copying a ConsString instead of flattening it to a
378 // SeqString makes no sense here (since flattening would be faster and use
379 // less memory). Thus, if one of {left} or {right} is a young string, we'll
380 // build a SeqString rather than a ConsString, regardless of {length}.
381 // TODO(dmercadier, dinfuehr): always build a ConsString here once the
382 // generational write-barrier supports background threads.
383 if (!LocalHeap::Current() || (!HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*left) &&
384 !HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*right))) {
385 return broker()
386 ->local_isolate_or_isolate()
387 ->factory()
388 ->NewConsString(left, right, AllocationType::kOld)
389 .ToHandleChecked();
390 }
391 }
392
393 // If one of the string is not in readonly space, then we need a
394 // SharedStringAccessGuardIfNeeded before accessing its content.
395 bool require_guard = SharedStringAccessGuardIfNeeded::IsNeeded(
396 *left, broker()->local_isolate_or_isolate()) ||
397 SharedStringAccessGuardIfNeeded::IsNeeded(
398 *right, broker()->local_isolate_or_isolate());
399 SharedStringAccessGuardIfNeeded access_guard(
400 require_guard ? broker()->local_isolate_or_isolate() : nullptr);
401
402 if (left->IsOneByteRepresentation() && right->IsOneByteRepresentation()) {
403 // {left} and {right} are 1-byte ==> the result will be 1-byte.
404 // Note that we need a canonical handle, because we insert in
405 // {created_strings_} the handle's address, which is kinda meaningless if
406 // the handle isn't canonical.
407 Handle<SeqOneByteString> flat = broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
408 broker()
409 ->local_isolate_or_isolate()
410 ->factory()
411 ->NewRawOneByteString(length, AllocationType::kOld)
412 .ToHandleChecked());
413 created_strings_.insert(flat);
414 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
415 String::WriteToFlat(*left, flat->GetChars(no_gc, access_guard), 0,
416 left->length(), access_guard);
417 String::WriteToFlat(*right,
418 flat->GetChars(no_gc, access_guard) + left->length(), 0,
419 right->length(), access_guard);
420 return flat;
421 } else {
422 // One (or both) of {left} and {right} is 2-byte ==> the result will be
423 // 2-byte.
424 Handle<SeqTwoByteString> flat = broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(
425 broker()
426 ->local_isolate_or_isolate()
427 ->factory()
428 ->NewRawTwoByteString(length, AllocationType::kOld)
429 .ToHandleChecked());
430 created_strings_.insert(flat);
431 DisallowGarbageCollection no_gc;
432 String::WriteToFlat(*left, flat->GetChars(no_gc, access_guard), 0,
433 left->length(), access_guard);
434 String::WriteToFlat(*right,
435 flat->GetChars(no_gc, access_guard) + left->length(), 0,
436 right->length(), access_guard);
437 return flat;
438 }
439}

441bool JSNativeContextSpecialization::StringCanSafelyBeRead(Node* const node,
442 Handle<String> str) {
443 DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kHeapConstant ||
444 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kNumberConstant);
445 if (broker()->IsMainThread()) {
446 // All strings are safe to be read on the main thread.
447 return true;
448 }
449 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kNumberConstant) {
450 // If {node} is a number constant, then {str} is the stringification of this
451 // number which we must have created ourselves.
452 return true;
453 }
454 return !IsStringWithNonAccessibleContent(broker(), node) ||
455 created_strings_.find(str) != created_strings_.end();
456}

458Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSAdd(Node* node) {
459 // TODO(turbofan): This has to run together with the inlining and
460 // native context specialization to be able to leverage the string
461 // constant-folding for optimizing property access, but we should
462 // nevertheless find a better home for this at some point.
463 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSAdd, node->opcode());
464
465 Node* const lhs = node->InputAt(0);
466 Node* const rhs = node->InputAt(1);
467
468 std::optional<size_t> lhs_len = GetMaxStringLength(broker(), lhs);
469 std::optional<size_t> rhs_len = GetMaxStringLength(broker(), rhs);
470 if (!lhs_len || !rhs_len) return NoChange();
471
472 // Fold if at least one of the parameters is a string constant and the
473 // addition won't throw due to too long result.
474 if (*lhs_len + *rhs_len <= String::kMaxLength &&
475 (IsStringConstant(broker(), lhs) || IsStringConstant(broker(), rhs))) {
476 // We need canonical handles for {left} and {right}, in order to be able to
477 // search {created_strings_} if needed.
478 Handle<String> left =
479 broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(CreateStringConstant(lhs));
480 Handle<String> right =
481 broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(CreateStringConstant(rhs));
482
483 if (!(StringCanSafelyBeRead(lhs, left) &&
484 StringCanSafelyBeRead(rhs, right))) {
485 // One of {lhs} or {rhs} is not safe to be read in the background.
486
487 if (left->length() + right->length() > ConsString::kMinLength &&
488 (!LocalHeap::Current() || (!HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*left) &&
489 !HeapLayout::InYoungGeneration(*right)))) {
490 // We can create a ConsString with {left} and {right}, without needing
491 // to read their content (and this ConsString will not introduce
492 // old-to-new pointers from the background).
493 Handle<String> concatenated =
494 broker()
495 ->local_isolate_or_isolate()
496 ->factory()
497 ->NewConsString(left, right, AllocationType::kOld)
498 .ToHandleChecked();
499 Node* reduced = graph()->NewNode(common()->HeapConstant(
500 broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(concatenated)));
501 ReplaceWithValue(node, reduced);
502 return Replace(reduced);
503 } else {
504 // Concatenating those strings would not produce a ConsString but rather
505 // a flat string (because the result is small). And, since the strings
506 // are not safe to be read in the background, this wouldn't be safe.
507 // Or, one of the string is in the young generation, and since the
508 // generational barrier doesn't support background threads, we cannot
509 // create the ConsString.
510 return NoChange();
511 }
512 }
513
514 Handle<String> concatenated = Concatenate(left, right);
515 Node* reduced = graph()->NewNode(common()->HeapConstant(
516 broker()->CanonicalPersistentHandle(concatenated)));
517
518 ReplaceWithValue(node, reduced);
519 return Replace(reduced);
520 }
521
522 return NoChange();
523}

525Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSGetSuperConstructor(
526 Node* node) {
527 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSGetSuperConstructor, node->opcode());
528 Node* constructor = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
529
530 // Check if the input is a known JSFunction.
531 HeapObjectMatcher m(constructor);
532 if (!m.HasResolvedValue() || !m.Ref(broker()).IsJSFunction()) {
533 return NoChange();
534 }
535 JSFunctionRef function = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSFunction();
536 MapRef function_map = function.map(broker());
537 HeapObjectRef function_prototype = function_map.prototype(broker());
538
539 // We can constant-fold the super constructor access if the
540 // {function}s map is stable, i.e. we can use a code dependency
541 // to guard against [[Prototype]] changes of {function}.
542 if (function_map.is_stable()) {
543 dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(function_map);
544 Node* value = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(function_prototype, broker());
545 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
546 return Replace(value);
547 }
548
549 return NoChange();
550}

552Reduction
553JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct(
554 Node* node) {
555 JSFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstructNode n(node);
556 Node* this_function = n.this_function();
557 Node* new_target = n.new_target();
558 Node* effect = n.effect();
559 Control control = n.control();
560
561 // If the JSFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct operation is inside a try
562 // catch, wiring up the graph is complex (reason: if
563 // JSFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct reduces to a constant which is
564 // something else than a default base ctor, it cannot throw an exception, and
565 // the try-catch structure has to be rewired). As this use case is rare, give
566 // up optimizing it here.
567 if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node)) {
568 return NoChange();
569 }
570
571 // TODO(v8:13091): Don't produce incomplete stack traces when debug is active.
572 // We already deopt when a breakpoint is set. But it would be even nicer to
573 // avoid producting incomplete stack traces when when debug is active, even if
574 // there are no breakpoints - then a user inspecting stack traces via Dev
575 // Tools would always see the full stack trace.
576
577 // Check if the input is a known JSFunction.
578 HeapObjectMatcher m(this_function);
579 if (!m.HasResolvedValue() || !m.Ref(broker()).IsJSFunction()) {
580 return NoChange();
581 }
582
583 JSFunctionRef this_function_ref = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSFunction();
584 MapRef function_map = this_function_ref.map(broker());
585 HeapObjectRef current = function_map.prototype(broker());
586 // The uppermost JSFunction on the class hierarchy (above it, there can be
587 // other JSObjects, e.g., Proxies).
588 OptionalJSObjectRef last_function;
589
590 Node* return_value;
591 Node* ctor_or_instance;
592
593 // Walk the class inheritance tree until we find a ctor which is not a default
594 // derived ctor.
595 while (true) {
596 if (!current.IsJSFunction()) {
597 return NoChange();
598 }
599 JSFunctionRef current_function = current.AsJSFunction();
600
601 // If there are class fields, bail out. TODO(v8:13091): Handle them here.
602 if (current_function.shared(broker())
603 .requires_instance_members_initializer()) {
604 return NoChange();
605 }
606
607 // If there are private methods, bail out. TODO(v8:13091): Handle them here.
608 if (current_function.context(broker())
609 .scope_info(broker())
610 .ClassScopeHasPrivateBrand()) {
611 return NoChange();
612 }
613
614 FunctionKind kind = current_function.shared(broker()).kind();
615
616 if (kind != FunctionKind::kDefaultDerivedConstructor) {
617 // The hierarchy walk will end here; this is the last change to bail out
618 // before creating new nodes.
619 if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayIteratorProtector()) {
620 return NoChange();
621 }
622 last_function = current_function;
623
624 if (kind == FunctionKind::kDefaultBaseConstructor) {
625 return_value = jsgraph()->BooleanConstant(true);
626
627 // Generate a builtin call for creating the instance.
628 Node* constructor =
629 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(current_function, broker());
630
631 // In the current FrameState setup, the two outputs of this bytecode are
632 // poked at indices slot(index(reg_2)) (boolean_output) and
633 // slot(index(reg_2) + 1) (object_output). Now we're reducing this
634 // bytecode to a builtin call which only has one output (object_output).
635 // Change where in the FrameState the output is poked at.
636
637 // The current poke location points to the location for boolean_ouput.
638 // We move the poke location by -1, since the poke location decreases
639 // when the register index increases (see
640 // BytecodeGraphBuilder::Environment::BindRegistersToProjections).
641
642 // The location for boolean_output is already hard-wired to true (which
643 // is the correct value here) in
644 // BytecodeGraphBuilder::VisitFindNonDefaultConstructorOrConstruct.
645
646 FrameState old_frame_state = n.frame_state();
647 auto old_poke_offset = old_frame_state.frame_state_info()
648 .state_combine()
649 .GetOffsetToPokeAt();
650 FrameState new_frame_state = CloneFrameState(
651 jsgraph(), old_frame_state,
652 OutputFrameStateCombine::PokeAt(old_poke_offset - 1));
653
654 effect = ctor_or_instance = graph()->NewNode(
655 jsgraph()->javascript()->Create(), constructor, new_target,
656 n.context(), new_frame_state, effect, control);
657 } else {
658 return_value = jsgraph()->BooleanConstant(false);
659 ctor_or_instance =
660 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(current_function, broker());
661 }
662 break;
663 }
664
665 // Keep walking up the class tree.
666 current = current_function.map(broker()).prototype(broker());
667 }
668
669 dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChain(
670 function_map, WhereToStart::kStartAtReceiver, last_function);
671
672 // Update the uses of {node}.
673 for (Edge edge : node->use_edges()) {
674 Node* const user = edge.from();
675 if (NodeProperties::IsEffectEdge(edge)) {
676 edge.UpdateTo(effect);
677 } else if (NodeProperties::IsControlEdge(edge)) {
678 edge.UpdateTo(control);
679 } else {
680 DCHECK(NodeProperties::IsValueEdge(edge));
681 switch (ProjectionIndexOf(user->op())) {
682 case 0:
683 Replace(user, return_value);
684 break;
685 case 1:
686 Replace(user, ctor_or_instance);
687 break;
688 default:
689 UNREACHABLE();
690 }
691 }
692 }
693 node->Kill();
694 return Replace(return_value);
695}

697Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSInstanceOf(Node* node) {
698 JSInstanceOfNode n(node);
699 FeedbackParameter const& p = n.Parameters();
700 Node* object = n.left();
701 Node* constructor = n.right();
702 TNode<Object> context = n.context();
703 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
704 Effect effect = n.effect();
705 Control control = n.control();
706
707 // Check if the right hand side is a known {receiver}, or
708 // we have feedback from the InstanceOfIC.
709 OptionalJSObjectRef receiver;
710 HeapObjectMatcher m(constructor);
711 if (m.HasResolvedValue() && m.Ref(broker()).IsJSObject()) {
712 receiver = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSObject();
713 } else if (p.feedback().IsValid()) {
714 ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
715 broker()->GetFeedbackForInstanceOf(FeedbackSource(p.feedback()));
716 if (feedback.IsInsufficient()) return NoChange();
717 receiver = feedback.AsInstanceOf().value();
718 } else {
719 return NoChange();
720 }
721
722 if (!receiver.has_value()) return NoChange();
723
724 MapRef receiver_map = receiver->map(broker());
725 NameRef name = broker()->has_instance_symbol();
726 PropertyAccessInfo access_info =
727 broker()->GetPropertyAccessInfo(receiver_map, name, AccessMode::kLoad);
728
729 // TODO(v8:11457) Support dictionary mode holders here.
730 if (access_info.IsInvalid() || access_info.HasDictionaryHolder()) {
731 return NoChange();
732 }
733 access_info.RecordDependencies(dependencies());
734
735 PropertyAccessBuilder access_builder(jsgraph(), broker());
736
737 if (access_info.IsNotFound()) {
738 // If there's no @@hasInstance handler, the OrdinaryHasInstance operation
739 // takes over, but that requires the constructor to be callable.
740 if (!receiver_map.is_callable()) return NoChange();
741
742 dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
743 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), kStartAtPrototype);
744
745 // Monomorphic property access.
746 access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(constructor, &effect, control,
747 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps());
748
749 // Lower to OrdinaryHasInstance(C, O).
750 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, constructor, 0);
751 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, object, 1);
752 NodeProperties::ReplaceEffectInput(node, effect);
753 static_assert(n.FeedbackVectorIndex() == 2);
754 node->RemoveInput(n.FeedbackVectorIndex());
755 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->OrdinaryHasInstance());
756 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSOrdinaryHasInstance(node));
757 }
758
759 if (access_info.IsFastDataConstant()) {
760 OptionalJSObjectRef holder = access_info.holder();
761 bool found_on_proto = holder.has_value();
762 JSObjectRef holder_ref = found_on_proto ? holder.value() : receiver.value();
763 if (access_info.field_representation().IsDouble()) return NoChange();
764 OptionalObjectRef constant = holder_ref.GetOwnFastConstantDataProperty(
765 broker(), access_info.field_representation(), access_info.field_index(),
766 dependencies());
767 if (!constant.has_value() || !constant->IsHeapObject() ||
768 !constant->AsHeapObject().map(broker()).is_callable()) {
769 return NoChange();
770 }
771
772 if (found_on_proto) {
773 dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
774 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), kStartAtPrototype,
775 holder.value());
776 }
777
778 // Check that {constructor} is actually {receiver}.
779 constructor = access_builder.BuildCheckValue(constructor, &effect, control,
780 *receiver);
781
782 // Monomorphic property access.
783 access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(constructor, &effect, control,
784 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps());
785
786 // Create a nested frame state inside the current method's most-recent frame
787 // state that will ensure that deopts that happen after this point will not
788 // fallback to the last Checkpoint--which would completely re-execute the
789 // instanceof logic--but rather create an activation of a version of the
790 // ToBoolean stub that finishes the remaining work of instanceof and returns
791 // to the caller without duplicating side-effects upon a lazy deopt.
792 Node* continuation_frame_state = CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
793 jsgraph(), Builtin::kToBooleanLazyDeoptContinuation, context, nullptr,
794 0, frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
795
796 // Call the @@hasInstance handler.
797 Node* target = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(*constant, broker());
798 Node* feedback = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
799 // Value inputs plus context, frame state, effect, control.
800 static_assert(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(1) + 4 == 8);
801 node->EnsureInputCount(graph()->zone(), 8);
802 node->ReplaceInput(JSCallNode::TargetIndex(), target);
803 node->ReplaceInput(JSCallNode::ReceiverIndex(), constructor);
804 node->ReplaceInput(JSCallNode::ArgumentIndex(0), object);
805 node->ReplaceInput(3, feedback);
806 node->ReplaceInput(4, context);
807 node->ReplaceInput(5, continuation_frame_state);
808 node->ReplaceInput(6, effect);
809 node->ReplaceInput(7, control);
810 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
811 node, javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(1), CallFrequency(),
812 FeedbackSource(),
813 ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined));
814
815 // Rewire the value uses of {node} to ToBoolean conversion of the result.
816 Node* value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ToBoolean(), node);
817 for (Edge edge : node->use_edges()) {
818 if (NodeProperties::IsValueEdge(edge) && edge.from() != value) {
819 edge.UpdateTo(value);
820 Revisit(edge.from());
821 }
822 }
823 return Changed(node);
824 }
825
826 return NoChange();
827}
828
829JSNativeContextSpecialization::InferHasInPrototypeChainResult
830JSNativeContextSpecialization::InferHasInPrototypeChain(
831 Node* receiver, Effect effect, HeapObjectRef prototype) {
832 ZoneRefSet<Map> receiver_maps;
833 NodeProperties::InferMapsResult result = NodeProperties::InferMapsUnsafe(
834 broker(), receiver, effect, &receiver_maps);
835 if (result == NodeProperties::kNoMaps) return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
836
837 ZoneVector<MapRef> receiver_map_refs(zone());
838
839 // Try to determine either that all of the {receiver_maps} have the given
840 // {prototype} in their chain, or that none do. If we can't tell, return
841 // kMayBeInPrototypeChain.
842 bool all = true;
843 bool none = true;
844 for (MapRef map : receiver_maps) {
845 receiver_map_refs.push_back(map);
846 if (result == NodeProperties::kUnreliableMaps && !map.is_stable()) {
847 return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
848 }
849 while (true) {
850 if (IsSpecialReceiverInstanceType(map.instance_type())) {
851 return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
852 }
853 if (!map.IsJSObjectMap()) {
854 all = false;
855 break;
856 }
857 HeapObjectRef map_prototype = map.prototype(broker());
858 if (map_prototype.equals(prototype)) {
859 none = false;
860 break;
861 }
862 map = map_prototype.map(broker());
863 // TODO(v8:11457) Support dictionary mode protoypes here.
864 if (!map.is_stable() || map.is_dictionary_map()) {
865 return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
866 }
867 if (map.oddball_type(broker()) == OddballType::kNull) {
868 all = false;
869 break;
870 }
871 }
872 }
873 DCHECK_IMPLIES(all, !none);
874 if (!all && !none) return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
875
876 {
877 OptionalJSObjectRef last_prototype;
878 if (all) {
879 // We don't need to protect the full chain if we found the prototype, we
880 // can stop at {prototype}. In fact we could stop at the one before
881 // {prototype} but since we're dealing with multiple receiver maps this
882 // might be a different object each time, so it's much simpler to include
883 // {prototype}. That does, however, mean that we must check {prototype}'s
884 // map stability.
885 if (!prototype.IsJSObject() || !prototype.map(broker()).is_stable()) {
886 return kMayBeInPrototypeChain;
887 }
888 last_prototype = prototype.AsJSObject();
889 }
890 WhereToStart start = result == NodeProperties::kUnreliableMaps
891 ? kStartAtReceiver
892 : kStartAtPrototype;
893 dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(receiver_map_refs, start,
894 last_prototype);
895 }
896
897 DCHECK_EQ(all, !none);
898 return all ? kIsInPrototypeChain : kIsNotInPrototypeChain;
899}
900
901Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSHasInPrototypeChain(
902 Node* node) {
903 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSHasInPrototypeChain, node->opcode());
904 Node* value = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
905 Node* prototype = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
906 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
907
908 // Check if we can constant-fold the prototype chain walk
909 // for the given {value} and the {prototype}.
910 HeapObjectMatcher m(prototype);
911 if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
912 InferHasInPrototypeChainResult result =
913 InferHasInPrototypeChain(value, effect, m.Ref(broker()));
914 if (result != kMayBeInPrototypeChain) {
915 Node* result_in_chain =
916 jsgraph()->BooleanConstant(result == kIsInPrototypeChain);
917 ReplaceWithValue(node, result_in_chain);
918 return Replace(result_in_chain);
919 }
920 }
921
922 return NoChange();
923}
924
925Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSOrdinaryHasInstance(
926 Node* node) {
927 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSOrdinaryHasInstance, node->opcode());
928 Node* constructor = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
929 Node* object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
930
931 // Check if the {constructor} is known at compile time.
932 HeapObjectMatcher m(constructor);
933 if (!m.HasResolvedValue()) return NoChange();
934
935 if (m.Ref(broker()).IsJSBoundFunction()) {
936 // OrdinaryHasInstance on bound functions turns into a recursive invocation
937 // of the instanceof operator again.
938 JSBoundFunctionRef function = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSBoundFunction();
939 Node* feedback = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
940 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, object,
941 JSInstanceOfNode::LeftIndex());
942 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(
943 node,
944 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(function.bound_target_function(broker()),
945 broker()),
946 JSInstanceOfNode::RightIndex());
947 node->InsertInput(zone(), JSInstanceOfNode::FeedbackVectorIndex(),
948 feedback);
949 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->InstanceOf(FeedbackSource()));
950 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSInstanceOf(node));
951 }
952
953 if (m.Ref(broker()).IsJSFunction()) {
954 // Optimize if we currently know the "prototype" property.
955
956 JSFunctionRef function = m.Ref(broker()).AsJSFunction();
957
958 // TODO(neis): Remove the has_prototype_slot condition once the broker is
959 // always enabled.
960 if (!function.map(broker()).has_prototype_slot() ||
961 !function.has_instance_prototype(broker()) ||
962 function.PrototypeRequiresRuntimeLookup(broker())) {
963 return NoChange();
964 }
965
966 HeapObjectRef prototype =
967 dependencies()->DependOnPrototypeProperty(function);
968 Node* prototype_constant = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(prototype, broker());
969
970 // Lower the {node} to JSHasInPrototypeChain.
971 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, object, 0);
972 NodeProperties::ReplaceValueInput(node, prototype_constant, 1);
973 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, javascript()->HasInPrototypeChain());
974 return Changed(node).FollowedBy(ReduceJSHasInPrototypeChain(node));
975 }
976
977 return NoChange();
978}

980// ES section #sec-promise-resolve
981Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSPromiseResolve(Node* node) {
982 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSPromiseResolve, node->opcode());
983 Node* constructor = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
984 Node* value = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
985 Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
986 FrameState frame_state{NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node)};
987 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
988 Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
989
990 // Check if the {constructor} is the %Promise% function.
991 HeapObjectMatcher m(constructor);
992 if (!m.HasResolvedValue() ||
993 !m.Ref(broker()).equals(native_context().promise_function(broker()))) {
994 return NoChange();
995 }
996
997 // Only optimize if {value} cannot be a JSPromise.
998 MapInference inference(broker(), value, effect);
999 if (!inference.HaveMaps() ||
1000 inference.AnyOfInstanceTypesAre(JS_PROMISE_TYPE)) {
1001 return NoChange();
1002 }
1003
1004 if (!dependencies()->DependOnPromiseHookProtector()) return NoChange();
1005
1006 // Create a %Promise% instance and resolve it with {value}.
1007 Node* promise = effect =
1008 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->CreatePromise(), context, effect);
1009
1010 // Create a nested frame state inside the current method's most-recent
1011 // {frame_state} that will ensure that lazy deoptimizations at this
1012 // point will still return the {promise} instead of the result of the
1013 // ResolvePromise operation (which yields undefined).
1014 Node* parameters[] = {promise};
1015 frame_state = CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
1016 jsgraph(), Builtin::kAsyncFunctionLazyDeoptContinuation, context,
1017 parameters, arraysize(parameters), frame_state,
1018 ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
1019
1020 effect = graph()->NewNode(javascript()->ResolvePromise(), promise, value,
1021 context, frame_state, effect, control);
1022 ReplaceWithValue(node, promise, effect, control);
1023 return Replace(promise);
1024}

1026// ES section #sec-promise-resolve-functions
1027Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSResolvePromise(Node* node) {
1028 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSResolvePromise, node->opcode());
1029 Node* promise = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
1030 Node* resolution = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1);
1031 Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
1032 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
1033 Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
1034
1035 // Check if we know something about the {resolution}.
1036 MapInference inference(broker(), resolution, effect);
1037 if (!inference.HaveMaps()) return NoChange();
1038 ZoneRefSet<Map> const& resolution_maps = inference.GetMaps();
1039
1040 // Compute property access info for "then" on {resolution}.
1041 ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> access_infos(graph()->zone());
1042 AccessInfoFactory access_info_factory(broker(), graph()->zone());
1043
1044 for (MapRef map : resolution_maps) {
1045 access_infos.push_back(broker()->GetPropertyAccessInfo(
1046 map, broker()->then_string(), AccessMode::kLoad));
1047 }
1048 PropertyAccessInfo access_info =
1049 access_info_factory.FinalizePropertyAccessInfosAsOne(access_infos,
1050 AccessMode::kLoad);
1051
1052 // TODO(v8:11457) Support dictionary mode prototypes here.
1053 if (access_info.IsInvalid() || access_info.HasDictionaryHolder()) {
1054 return inference.NoChange();
1055 }
1056
1057 // Only optimize when {resolution} definitely doesn't have a "then" property.
1058 if (!access_info.IsNotFound()) return inference.NoChange();
1059
1060 if (!inference.RelyOnMapsViaStability(dependencies())) {
1061 return inference.NoChange();
1062 }
1063
1064 dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
1065 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), kStartAtPrototype);
1066
1067 // Simply fulfill the {promise} with the {resolution}.
1068 Node* value = effect =
1069 graph()->NewNode(javascript()->FulfillPromise(), promise, resolution,
1070 context, effect, control);
1071 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
1072 return Replace(value);
1073}

1094// TODO(neis): Try to merge this with ReduceNamedAccess by introducing a new
1095// PropertyAccessInfo kind for global accesses and using the existing mechanism
1096// for building loads/stores.
1097// Note: The "receiver" parameter is only used for DCHECKS, but that's on
1098// purpose. This way we can assert the super property access cases won't hit the
1099// code which hasn't been modified to support super property access.
1100Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceGlobalAccess(
1101 Node* node, Node* lookup_start_object, Node* receiver, Node* value,
1102 NameRef name, AccessMode access_mode, Node* key,
1103 PropertyCellRef property_cell, Node* effect) {
1104 if (!property_cell.Cache(broker())) {
1105 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "usable data for " << property_cell);
1106 return NoChange();
1107 }
1108
1109 ObjectRef property_cell_value = property_cell.value(broker());
1110 if (property_cell_value.IsPropertyCellHole()) {
1111 // The property cell is no longer valid.
1112 return NoChange();
1113 }
1114
1115 PropertyDetails property_details = property_cell.property_details();
1116 PropertyCellType property_cell_type = property_details.cell_type();
1117 DCHECK_EQ(PropertyKind::kData, property_details.kind());
1118
1119 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
1120 if (effect == nullptr) {
1121 effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
1122 }
1123
1124 // We have additional constraints for stores.
1125 if (access_mode == AccessMode::kStore) {
1126 DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
1127 if (property_details.IsReadOnly()) {
1128 // Don't even bother trying to lower stores to read-only data properties.
1129 // TODO(neis): We could generate code that checks if the new value equals
1130 // the old one and then does nothing or deopts, respectively.
1131 return NoChange();
1132 } else if (property_cell_type == PropertyCellType::kUndefined) {
1133 return NoChange();
1134 } else if (property_cell_type == PropertyCellType::kConstantType) {
1135 // We rely on stability further below.
1136 if (property_cell_value.IsHeapObject() &&
1137 !property_cell_value.AsHeapObject().map(broker()).is_stable()) {
1138 return NoChange();
1139 }
1140 }
1141 } else if (access_mode == AccessMode::kHas) {
1142 DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
1143 // has checks cannot follow the fast-path used by loads when these
1144 // conditions hold.
1145 if ((property_details.IsConfigurable() || !property_details.IsReadOnly()) &&
1146 property_details.cell_type() != PropertyCellType::kConstant &&
1147 property_details.cell_type() != PropertyCellType::kUndefined)
1148 return NoChange();
1149 }
1150
1151 // Ensure that {key} matches the specified {name} (if {key} is given).
1152 if (key != nullptr) {
1153 effect = BuildCheckEqualsName(name, key, effect, control);
1154 }
1155
1156 // If we have a {lookup_start_object} to validate, we do so by checking that
1157 // its map is the (target) global proxy's map. This guarantees that in fact
1158 // the lookup start object is the global proxy.
1159 // Note: we rely on the map constant below being the same as what is used in
1160 // NativeContextRef::GlobalIsDetached().
1161 if (lookup_start_object != nullptr) {
1162 effect = graph()->NewNode(
1163 simplified()->CheckMaps(
1164 CheckMapsFlag::kNone,
1165 ZoneRefSet<Map>(
1166 native_context().global_proxy_object(broker()).map(broker()))),
1167 lookup_start_object, effect, control);
1168 }
1169
1170 if (access_mode == AccessMode::kLoad || access_mode == AccessMode::kHas) {
1171 // Load from non-configurable, read-only data property on the global
1172 // object can be constant-folded, even without deoptimization support.
1173 if (!property_details.IsConfigurable() && property_details.IsReadOnly()) {
1174 value = access_mode == AccessMode::kHas
1175 ? jsgraph()->TrueConstant()
1176 : jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(property_cell_value, broker());
1177 } else {
1178 // Record a code dependency on the cell if we can benefit from the
1179 // additional feedback, or the global property is configurable (i.e.
1180 // can be deleted or reconfigured to an accessor property).
1181 if (property_details.cell_type() != PropertyCellType::kMutable ||
1182 property_details.IsConfigurable()) {
1183 dependencies()->DependOnGlobalProperty(property_cell);
1184 }
1185
1186 // Load from constant/undefined global property can be constant-folded.
1187 if (property_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kConstant ||
1188 property_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kUndefined) {
1189 value = access_mode == AccessMode::kHas
1190 ? jsgraph()->TrueConstant()
1191 : jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(property_cell_value, broker());
1192 DCHECK(!property_cell_value.IsHeapObject() ||
1193 !property_cell_value.IsPropertyCellHole());
1194 } else {
1195 DCHECK_NE(AccessMode::kHas, access_mode);
1196
1197 // Load from constant type cell can benefit from type feedback.
1198 OptionalMapRef map;
1199 Type property_cell_value_type = Type::NonInternal();
1200 MachineRepresentation representation = MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
1201 if (property_details.cell_type() == PropertyCellType::kConstantType) {
1202 // Compute proper type based on the current value in the cell.
1203 if (property_cell_value.IsSmi()) {
1204 property_cell_value_type = Type::SignedSmall();
1205 representation = MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned;
1206 } else if (property_cell_value.IsHeapNumber()) {
1207 property_cell_value_type = Type::Number();
1208 representation = MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer;
1209 } else {
1210 MapRef property_cell_value_map =
1211 property_cell_value.AsHeapObject().map(broker());
1212 property_cell_value_type =
1213 Type::For(property_cell_value_map, broker());
1214 representation = MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer;
1215
1216 // We can only use the property cell value map for map check
1217 // elimination if it's stable, i.e. the HeapObject wasn't
1218 // mutated without the cell state being updated.
1219 if (property_cell_value_map.is_stable()) {
1220 dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(property_cell_value_map);
1221 map = property_cell_value_map;
1222 }
1223 }
1224 }
1225 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
1226 simplified()->LoadField(ForPropertyCellValue(
1227 representation, property_cell_value_type, map, name)),
1228 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(property_cell, broker()), effect,
1229 control);
1230 }
1231 }
1232 } else if (access_mode == AccessMode::kStore) {
1233 DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
1234 DCHECK(!property_details.IsReadOnly());
1235 switch (property_details.cell_type()) {
1236 case PropertyCellType::kConstant: {
1237 // Record a code dependency on the cell, and just deoptimize if the new
1238 // value doesn't match the previous value stored inside the cell.
1239 dependencies()->DependOnGlobalProperty(property_cell);
1240 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(
1241 simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), value,
1242 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(property_cell_value, broker()));
1243 effect = graph()->NewNode(
1244 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kValueMismatch), check,
1245 effect, control);
1246 break;
1247 }
1248 case PropertyCellType::kConstantType: {
1249 // Record a code dependency on the cell, and just deoptimize if the new
1250 // value's type doesn't match the type of the previous value in the
1251 // cell.
1252 dependencies()->DependOnGlobalProperty(property_cell);
1253 Type property_cell_value_type;
1254 MachineRepresentation representation = MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
1255 if (property_cell_value.IsHeapObject()) {
1256 MapRef property_cell_value_map =
1257 property_cell_value.AsHeapObject().map(broker());
1258 dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(property_cell_value_map);
1259
1260 // Check that the {value} is a HeapObject.
1261 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckHeapObject(),
1262 value, effect, control);
1263 // Check {value} map against the {property_cell_value} map.
1264 effect = graph()->NewNode(
1265 simplified()->CheckMaps(CheckMapsFlag::kNone,
1266 ZoneRefSet<Map>(property_cell_value_map)),
1267 value, effect, control);
1268 property_cell_value_type = Type::OtherInternal();
1269 representation = MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer;
1270 } else {
1271 // Check that the {value} is a Smi.
1272 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
1273 simplified()->CheckSmi(FeedbackSource()), value, effect, control);
1274 property_cell_value_type = Type::SignedSmall();
1275 representation = MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned;
1276 }
1277 effect =
1278 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(ForPropertyCellValue(
1279 representation, property_cell_value_type,
1280 OptionalMapRef(), name)),
1281 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(property_cell, broker()),
1282 value, effect, control);
1283 break;
1284 }
1285 case PropertyCellType::kMutable: {
1286 // Record a code dependency on the cell, and just deoptimize if the
1287 // property ever becomes read-only.
1288 dependencies()->DependOnGlobalProperty(property_cell);
1289 effect =
1290 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(ForPropertyCellValue(
1291 MachineRepresentation::kTagged,
1292 Type::NonInternal(), OptionalMapRef(), name)),
1293 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(property_cell, broker()),
1294 value, effect, control);
1295 break;
1296 }
1297 case PropertyCellType::kUndefined:
1298 case PropertyCellType::kInTransition:
1299 UNREACHABLE();
1300 }
1301 } else {
1302 return NoChange();
1303 }
1304
1305 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
1306 return Replace(value);
1307}

1309Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSLoadGlobal(Node* node) {
1310 JSLoadGlobalNode n(node);
1311 LoadGlobalParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
1312 if (!p.feedback().IsValid()) return NoChange();
1313
1314 ProcessedFeedback const& processed =
1315 broker()->GetFeedbackForGlobalAccess(FeedbackSource(p.feedback()));
1316 if (processed.IsInsufficient()) return NoChange();
1317
1318 GlobalAccessFeedback const& feedback = processed.AsGlobalAccess();
1319 if (feedback.IsScriptContextSlot()) {
1320 Effect effect = n.effect();
1321 Control control = n.control();
1322 Node* script_context =
1323 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(feedback.script_context(), broker());
1324 Node* value;
1325 if (feedback.immutable()) {
1326 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
1327 javascript()->LoadContext(0, feedback.slot_index(), true),
1328 script_context, effect);
1329 } else {
1330 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
1331 javascript()->LoadScriptContext(0, feedback.slot_index()),
1332 script_context, effect, control);
1333 }
1334 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
1335 return Replace(value);
1336 } else if (feedback.IsPropertyCell()) {
1337 return ReduceGlobalAccess(node, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr, p.name(),
1338 AccessMode::kLoad, nullptr,
1339 feedback.property_cell());
1340 } else {
1341 DCHECK(feedback.IsMegamorphic());
1342 return NoChange();
1343 }
1344}

1346Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSStoreGlobal(Node* node) {
1347 JSStoreGlobalNode n(node);
1348 StoreGlobalParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
1349 Node* value = n.value();
1350 if (!p.feedback().IsValid()) return NoChange();
1351
1352 ProcessedFeedback const& processed =
1353 broker()->GetFeedbackForGlobalAccess(FeedbackSource(p.feedback()));
1354 if (processed.IsInsufficient()) return NoChange();
1355
1356 GlobalAccessFeedback const& feedback = processed.AsGlobalAccess();
1357 if (feedback.IsScriptContextSlot()) {
1358 if (feedback.immutable()) return NoChange();
1359 Node* effect = n.effect();
1360 Node* control = n.control();
1361 Node* script_context =
1362 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(feedback.script_context(), broker());
1363 effect = control = graph()->NewNode(
1364 javascript()->StoreScriptContext(0, feedback.slot_index()), value,
1365 script_context, effect, control);
1366 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
1367 return Replace(value);
1368 } else if (feedback.IsPropertyCell()) {
1369 return ReduceGlobalAccess(node, nullptr, nullptr, value, p.name(),
1370 AccessMode::kStore, nullptr,
1371 feedback.property_cell());
1372 } else {
1373 DCHECK(feedback.IsMegamorphic());
1374 return NoChange();
1375 }
1376}
1377
1378Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceMegaDOMPropertyAccess(
1379 Node* node, Node* value, MegaDOMPropertyAccessFeedback const& feedback,
1380 FeedbackSource const& source) {
1381 DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamed ||
1382 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadProperty);
1383 // TODO(mslekova): Add support and tests for kJSLoadNamedFromSuper.
1384 static_assert(JSLoadNamedNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1385 JSLoadPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0,
1386 "Assumptions about ObjectIndex have changed, please update "
1387 "this function.");
1388
1389 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
1390 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
1391 Node* frame_state = NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node);
1392
1393 Node* lookup_start_object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
1394
1395 if (!dependencies()->DependOnMegaDOMProtector()) {
1396 return NoChange();
1397 }
1398
1399 FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info = feedback.info();
1400 int16_t range_start =
1401 function_template_info.allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_start();
1402 int16_t range_end =
1403 function_template_info.allowed_receiver_instance_type_range_end();
1404 DCHECK_IMPLIES(range_start == 0, range_end == 0);
1405 DCHECK_LE(range_start, range_end);
1406
1407 // TODO(mslekova): This could be a new InstanceTypeCheck operator
1408 // that gets lowered later on (e.g. during generic lowering).
1409 Node* receiver_map = effect =
1410 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()),
1411 lookup_start_object, effect, control);
1412 Node* receiver_instance_type = effect = graph()->NewNode(
1413 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapInstanceType()),
1414 receiver_map, effect, control);
1415
1416 if (v8_flags.experimental_embedder_instance_types && range_start != 0) {
1417 // Embedder instance ID is set, doing a simple range check.
1418 Node* diff_to_start =
1419 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSubtract(), receiver_instance_type,
1420 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(range_start));
1421 Node* range_length = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(range_end - range_start);
1422
1423 // TODO(mslekova): Once we have the InstanceTypeCheck operator, we could
1424 // lower it to Uint32LessThan later on to perform what is done in bounds.h.
1425 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThanOrEqual(),
1426 diff_to_start, range_length);
1427 effect = graph()->NewNode(
1428 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongInstanceType), check,
1429 effect, control);
1430 } else if (function_template_info.is_signature_undefined(broker())) {
1431 // Signature is undefined, enough to check if the receiver is a JSApiObject.
1432 Node* check =
1433 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberEqual(), receiver_instance_type,
1434 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JS_API_OBJECT_TYPE));
1435 effect = graph()->NewNode(
1436 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongInstanceType), check,
1437 effect, control);
1438 } else {
1439 // Calling out to builtin to do signature check.
1440 Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(
1441 isolate(), Builtin::kCallFunctionTemplate_CheckCompatibleReceiver);
1442 int stack_arg_count = callable.descriptor().GetStackParameterCount() +
1443 1 /* implicit receiver */;
1444
1445 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
1446 graph()->zone(), callable.descriptor(), stack_arg_count,
1447 CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState, Operator::kNoProperties);
1448
1449 Node* inputs[8] = {
1450 jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(callable.code()),
1451 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(function_template_info, broker()),
1452 jsgraph()->Int32Constant(stack_arg_count),
1453 lookup_start_object,
1454 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(native_context(), broker()),
1455 frame_state,
1456 effect,
1457 control};
1458
1459 value = effect = control =
1460 graph()->NewNode(common()->Call(call_descriptor), 8, inputs);
1461 return Replace(value);
1462 }
1463
1464 value = InlineApiCall(lookup_start_object, lookup_start_object, frame_state,
1465 nullptr /*value*/, &effect, &control,
1466 function_template_info, source);
1467 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
1468 return Replace(value);
1469}
1470
1471Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceNamedAccess(
1472 Node* node, Node* value, NamedAccessFeedback const& feedback,
1473 AccessMode access_mode, Node* key) {
1474 DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamed ||
1475 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSSetNamedProperty ||
1476 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadProperty ||
1477 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSSetKeyedProperty ||
1478 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineNamedOwnProperty ||
1479 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral ||
1480 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSHasProperty ||
1481 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamedFromSuper ||
1482 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnProperty);
1483 static_assert(JSLoadNamedNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1484 JSSetNamedPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1485 JSLoadPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1486 JSSetKeyedPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1487 JSDefineNamedOwnPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1488 JSSetNamedPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1489 JSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteralNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1490 JSHasPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
1491 JSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0);
1492 static_assert(JSLoadNamedFromSuperNode::ReceiverIndex() == 0);
1493
1494 Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
1495 FrameState frame_state{NodeProperties::GetFrameStateInput(node)};
1496 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
1497 Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
1498
1499 // receiver = the object we pass to the accessor (if any) as the "this" value.
1500 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
1501 // lookup_start_object = the object where we start looking for the property.
1502 Node* lookup_start_object;
1503 if (node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamedFromSuper) {
1504 DCHECK(v8_flags.super_ic);
1505 JSLoadNamedFromSuperNode n(node);
1506 // Lookup start object is the __proto__ of the home object.
1507 lookup_start_object = effect =
1508 BuildLoadPrototypeFromObject(n.home_object(), effect, control);
1509 } else {
1510 lookup_start_object = receiver;
1511 }
1512
1513 // Either infer maps from the graph or use the feedback.
1514 ZoneVector<MapRef> inferred_maps(zone());
1515 if (!InferMaps(lookup_start_object, effect, &inferred_maps)) {
1516 for (MapRef map : feedback.maps()) {
1517 inferred_maps.push_back(map);
1518 }
1519 }
1520 RemoveImpossibleMaps(lookup_start_object, &inferred_maps);
1521
1522 // Check if we have an access o.x or o.x=v where o is the target native
1523 // contexts' global proxy, and turn that into a direct access to the
1524 // corresponding global object instead.
1525 if (inferred_maps.size() == 1) {
1526 MapRef lookup_start_object_map = inferred_maps[0];
1527 if (lookup_start_object_map.equals(
1528 native_context().global_proxy_object(broker()).map(broker()))) {
1529 if (!native_context().GlobalIsDetached(broker())) {
1530 OptionalPropertyCellRef cell =
1531 native_context().global_object(broker()).GetPropertyCell(
1532 broker(), feedback.name());
1533 if (!cell.has_value()) return NoChange();
1534 // Note: The map check generated by ReduceGlobalAccesses ensures that we
1535 // will deopt when/if GlobalIsDetached becomes true.
1536 return ReduceGlobalAccess(node, lookup_start_object, receiver, value,
1537 feedback.name(), access_mode, key, *cell,
1538 effect);
1539 }
1540 }
1541 }
1542
1543 ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> access_infos(zone());
1544 {
1545 ZoneVector<PropertyAccessInfo> access_infos_for_feedback(zone());
1546 for (MapRef map : inferred_maps) {
1547 if (map.is_deprecated()) continue;
1548
1549 // TODO(v8:12547): Support writing to objects in shared space, which need
1550 // a write barrier that calls Object::Share to ensure the RHS is shared.
1551 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(
1552 map.instance_type()) &&
1553 access_mode == AccessMode::kStore) {
1554 return NoChange();
1555 }
1556
1557 PropertyAccessInfo access_info =
1558 broker()->GetPropertyAccessInfo(map, feedback.name(), access_mode);
1559 access_infos_for_feedback.push_back(access_info);
1560 }
1561
1562 AccessInfoFactory access_info_factory(broker(), graph()->zone());
1563 if (!access_info_factory.FinalizePropertyAccessInfos(
1564 access_infos_for_feedback, access_mode, &access_infos)) {
1565 return NoChange();
1566 }
1567 }
1568
1569 // Ensure that {key} matches the specified name (if {key} is given).
1570 if (key != nullptr) {
1571 effect = BuildCheckEqualsName(feedback.name(), key, effect, control);
1572 }
1573
1574 // Collect call nodes to rewire exception edges.
1575 ZoneVector<Node*> if_exception_nodes(zone());
1576 ZoneVector<Node*>* if_exceptions = nullptr;
1577 Node* if_exception = nullptr;
1578 if (NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &if_exception)) {
1579 if_exceptions = &if_exception_nodes;
1580 }
1581
1582 PropertyAccessBuilder access_builder(jsgraph(), broker());
1583
1584 // Check for the monomorphic cases.
1585 if (access_infos.size() == 1) {
1586 PropertyAccessInfo access_info = access_infos.front();
1587 if (receiver != lookup_start_object) {
1588 // Super property access. lookup_start_object is a JSReceiver or
1589 // null. It can't be a number, a string etc. So trying to build the
1590 // checks in the "else if" branch doesn't make sense.
1591
1592 access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(
1593 lookup_start_object, &effect, control,
1594 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(),
1595 feedback.has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target());
1596
1597 if (HasOnlyStringWrapperMaps(broker(),
1598 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps())) {
1599 // In order to be able to use StringWrapperLength, we need a TypeGuard
1600 // when all input maps are StringWrapper maps.
1601 lookup_start_object = effect =
1602 graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::StringWrapper()),
1603 lookup_start_object, effect, control);
1604 }
1605
1606 } else if (!access_builder.TryBuildStringCheck(
1607 broker(), access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), &receiver,
1608 &effect, control) &&
1609 !access_builder.TryBuildNumberCheck(
1610 broker(), access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), &receiver,
1611 &effect, control)) {
1612 // Try to build string check or number check if possible. Otherwise build
1613 // a map check.
1614
1615 // TryBuildStringCheck and TryBuildNumberCheck don't update the receiver
1616 // if they fail.
1617 DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
1618 if (HasNumberMaps(broker(), access_info.lookup_start_object_maps())) {
1619 // We need to also let Smi {receiver}s through in this case, so
1620 // we construct a diamond, guarded by the Sminess of the {receiver}
1621 // and if {receiver} is not a Smi just emit a sequence of map checks.
1622 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), receiver);
1623 Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, control);
1624
1625 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
1626 Node* etrue = effect;
1627
1628 Control if_false{graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch)};
1629 Effect efalse = effect;
1630 access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(
1631 receiver, &efalse, if_false, access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(),
1632 feedback.has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target());
1633
1634 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
1635 effect =
1636 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
1637 } else {
1638 access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(
1639 receiver, &effect, control, access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(),
1640 feedback.has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target());
1641 }
1642
1643 if (HasOnlyStringWrapperMaps(broker(),
1644 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps())) {
1645 // In order to be able to use StringWrapperLength, we need a TypeGuard
1646 // when all input maps are StringWrapper maps. Note that, alternatively,
1647 // we could have a CheckStringWrapper, but it makes things simpler to
1648 // just rely on CheckMaps. This is slightly suboptimal in case the code
1649 // contains multiple string wrappers with different properties, but this
1650 // should be a rare case.
1651 lookup_start_object = receiver = effect =
1652 graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::StringWrapper()),
1653 lookup_start_object, effect, control);
1654 }
1655 } else {
1656 // At least one of TryBuildStringCheck & TryBuildNumberCheck succeeded
1657 // and updated the receiver. Update lookup_start_object to match (they
1658 // should be the same).
1659 lookup_start_object = receiver;
1660 }
1661
1662 // Generate the actual property access.
1663 std::optional<ValueEffectControl> continuation = BuildPropertyAccess(
1664 lookup_start_object, receiver, value, context, frame_state, effect,
1665 control, feedback.name(), if_exceptions, access_info, access_mode);
1666 if (!continuation) {
1667 // At this point we maybe have added nodes into the graph (e.g. via
1668 // NewNode or BuildCheckMaps) in some cases but we haven't connected them
1669 // to End since we haven't called ReplaceWithValue. Since they are nodes
1670 // which are not connected with End, they will be removed by graph
1671 // trimming.
1672 return NoChange();
1673 }
1674 value = continuation->value();
1675 effect = continuation->effect();
1676 control = continuation->control();
1677 } else {
1678 // The final states for every polymorphic branch. We join them with
1679 // Merge+Phi+EffectPhi at the bottom.
1680 ZoneVector<Node*> values(zone());
1681 ZoneVector<Node*> effects(zone());
1682 ZoneVector<Node*> controls(zone());
1683
1684 Node* receiverissmi_control = nullptr;
1685 Node* receiverissmi_effect = effect;
1686
1687 if (receiver == lookup_start_object) {
1688 // Check if {receiver} may be a number.
1689 bool receiverissmi_possible = false;
1690 for (PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info : access_infos) {
1691 if (HasNumberMaps(broker(), access_info.lookup_start_object_maps())) {
1692 receiverissmi_possible = true;
1693 break;
1694 }
1695 }
1696
1697 // Handle the case that {receiver} may be a number.
1698 if (receiverissmi_possible) {
1699 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), receiver);
1700 Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, control);
1701 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
1702 receiverissmi_control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
1703 receiverissmi_effect = effect;
1704 }
1705 }
1706
1707 // Generate code for the various different property access patterns.
1708 Node* fallthrough_control = control;
1709 for (size_t j = 0; j < access_infos.size(); ++j) {
1710 PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info = access_infos[j];
1711 Node* this_value = value;
1712 Node* this_lookup_start_object = lookup_start_object;
1713 Node* this_receiver = receiver;
1714 Effect this_effect = effect;
1715 Control this_control{fallthrough_control};
1716
1717 // Perform map check on {lookup_start_object}.
1718 ZoneVector<MapRef> const& lookup_start_object_maps =
1719 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps();
1720 {
1721 // Whether to insert a dedicated MapGuard node into the
1722 // effect to be able to learn from the control flow.
1723 bool insert_map_guard = true;
1724
1725 // Check maps for the {lookup_start_object}s.
1726 if (j == access_infos.size() - 1) {
1727 // Last map check on the fallthrough control path, do a
1728 // conditional eager deoptimization exit here.
1729 access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(
1730 lookup_start_object, &this_effect, this_control,
1731 lookup_start_object_maps,
1732 feedback.has_deprecated_map_without_migration_target());
1733 fallthrough_control = nullptr;
1734
1735 // Don't insert a MapGuard in this case, as the CheckMaps
1736 // node already gives you all the information you need
1737 // along the effect chain.
1738 insert_map_guard = false;
1739 } else {
1740 // Explicitly branch on the {lookup_start_object_maps}.
1741 ZoneRefSet<Map> maps(lookup_start_object_maps.begin(),
1742 lookup_start_object_maps.end(), graph()->zone());
1743 Node* check = this_effect =
1744 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CompareMaps(maps),
1745 lookup_start_object, this_effect, this_control);
1746 Node* branch =
1747 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, this_control);
1748 fallthrough_control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
1749 this_control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
1750 }
1751
1752 // The Number case requires special treatment to also deal with Smis.
1753 if (HasNumberMaps(broker(), lookup_start_object_maps)) {
1754 // Join this check with the "receiver is smi" check above.
1755 DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
1756 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(receiverissmi_effect);
1757 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(receiverissmi_control);
1758 this_control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), this_control,
1759 receiverissmi_control);
1760 this_effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), this_effect,
1761 receiverissmi_effect, this_control);
1762 receiverissmi_effect = receiverissmi_control = nullptr;
1763
1764 // The {lookup_start_object} can also be a Smi in this case, so
1765 // a MapGuard doesn't make sense for this at all.
1766 insert_map_guard = false;
1767 }
1768
1769 // Introduce a MapGuard to learn from this on the effect chain.
1770 if (insert_map_guard) {
1771 ZoneRefSet<Map> maps(lookup_start_object_maps.begin(),
1772 lookup_start_object_maps.end(), graph()->zone());
1773 this_effect =
1774 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->MapGuard(maps),
1775 lookup_start_object, this_effect, this_control);
1776 }
1777
1778 // If all {lookup_start_object_maps} are Strings we also need to rename
1779 // the {lookup_start_object} here to make sure that TurboFan knows that
1780 // along this path the {this_lookup_start_object} is a String. This is
1781 // because we want strict checking of types, for example for
1782 // StringLength operators.
1783 if (HasOnlyStringMaps(broker(), lookup_start_object_maps)) {
1784 DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
1785 this_lookup_start_object = this_receiver = this_effect =
1786 graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::String()),
1787 lookup_start_object, this_effect, this_control);
1788 } else if (HasOnlyStringWrapperMaps(broker(),
1789 lookup_start_object_maps)) {
1790 bool receiver_is_lookup_start =
1791 this_lookup_start_object == this_receiver;
1792 DCHECK_IMPLIES(access_mode != AccessMode::kLoad,
1793 receiver_is_lookup_start);
1794 this_lookup_start_object = this_effect =
1795 graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::StringWrapper()),
1796 lookup_start_object, this_effect, this_control);
1797 if (receiver_is_lookup_start) {
1798 this_receiver = this_lookup_start_object;
1799 }
1800 }
1801 }
1802
1803 // Generate the actual property access.
1804 std::optional<ValueEffectControl> continuation = BuildPropertyAccess(
1805 this_lookup_start_object, this_receiver, this_value, context,
1806 frame_state, this_effect, this_control, feedback.name(),
1807 if_exceptions, access_info, access_mode);
1808 if (!continuation) {
1809 // At this point we maybe have added nodes into the graph (e.g. via
1810 // NewNode or BuildCheckMaps) in some cases but we haven't connected
1811 // them to End since we haven't called ReplaceWithValue. Since they are
1812 // nodes which are not connected with End, they will be removed by graph
1813 // trimming.
1814 return NoChange();
1815 }
1816
1817 values.push_back(continuation->value());
1818 effects.push_back(continuation->effect());
1819 controls.push_back(continuation->control());
1820 }
1821
1822 DCHECK_NULL(fallthrough_control);
1823
1824 // Generate the final merge point for all (polymorphic) branches.
1825 int const control_count = static_cast<int>(controls.size());
1826 if (control_count == 0) {
1827 value = effect = control = jsgraph()->Dead();
1828 } else if (control_count == 1) {
1829 value = values.front();
1830 effect = effects.front();
1831 control = controls.front();
1832 } else {
1833 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(control_count), control_count,
1834 &controls.front());
1835 values.push_back(control);
1836 value = graph()->NewNode(
1837 common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, control_count),
1838 control_count + 1, &values.front());
1839 effects.push_back(control);
1840 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(control_count),
1841 control_count + 1, &effects.front());
1842 }
1843 }
1844
1845 // Properly rewire IfException edges if {node} is inside a try-block.
1846 if (!if_exception_nodes.empty()) {
1847 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(if_exception);
1848 DCHECK_EQ(if_exceptions, &if_exception_nodes);
1849 int const if_exception_count = static_cast<int>(if_exceptions->size());
1850 Node* merge = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(if_exception_count),
1851 if_exception_count, &if_exceptions->front());
1852 if_exceptions->push_back(merge);
1853 Node* ephi =
1854 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(if_exception_count),
1855 if_exception_count + 1, &if_exceptions->front());
1856 Node* phi = graph()->NewNode(
1857 common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, if_exception_count),
1858 if_exception_count + 1, &if_exceptions->front());
1859 ReplaceWithValue(if_exception, phi, ephi, merge);
1860 }
1861
1862 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
1863 return Replace(value);
1864}

1866Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSLoadNamed(Node* node) {
1867 JSLoadNamedNode n(node);
1868 NamedAccess const& p = n.Parameters();
1869 Node* const receiver = n.object();
1870 NameRef name = p.name();
1871
1872 // Check if we have a constant receiver.
1873 HeapObjectMatcher m(receiver);
1874 if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
1875 ObjectRef object = m.Ref(broker());
1876 if (object.IsJSFunction() && name.equals(broker()->prototype_string())) {
1877 // Optimize "prototype" property of functions.
1878 JSFunctionRef function = object.AsJSFunction();
1879 // TODO(neis): Remove the has_prototype_slot condition once the broker is
1880 // always enabled.
1881 if (!function.map(broker()).has_prototype_slot() ||
1882 !function.has_instance_prototype(broker()) ||
1883 function.PrototypeRequiresRuntimeLookup(broker())) {
1884 return NoChange();
1885 }
1886 HeapObjectRef prototype =
1887 dependencies()->DependOnPrototypeProperty(function);
1888 Node* value = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(prototype, broker());
1889 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
1890 return Replace(value);
1891 } else if (object.IsString() && name.equals(broker()->length_string())) {
1892 // Constant-fold "length" property on constant strings.
1893 Node* value = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(object.AsString().length());
1894 ReplaceWithValue(node, value);
1895 return Replace(value);
1896 }
1897 }
1898
1899 if (!p.feedback().IsValid()) return NoChange();
1900 return ReducePropertyAccess(node, nullptr, name, jsgraph()->Dead(),
1901 FeedbackSource(p.feedback()), AccessMode::kLoad);
1902}
