1914
1915Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSGetIterator(Node* node) {
1916 JSGetIteratorNode n(node);
1917 GetIteratorParameters const& p = n.Parameters();
1918
1919 TNode<Object> receiver = n.receiver();
1920 TNode<Object> context = n.context();
1921 FrameState frame_state = n.frame_state();
1922 Effect effect = n.effect();
1923 Control control = n.control();
1924
1925 Node* iterator_exception_node = nullptr;
1926 Node* if_exception_merge = nullptr;
1927 Node* if_exception_effect_phi = nullptr;
1928 Node* if_exception_phi = nullptr;
1929 bool has_exception_node =
1930 NodeProperties::IsExceptionalCall(node, &iterator_exception_node);
1931 int exception_node_index = 0;
1932 if (has_exception_node) {
1933 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(iterator_exception_node);
1934 // If there exists an IfException node for the iterator node, we need
1935 // to merge all the desugared nodes exception. The iterator node will be
1936 // desugared to LoadNamed, Call, CallRuntime, we can pre-allocate the
1937 // nodes with 4 inputs here and we use dead_node as a placeholder for the
1938 // input, which will be replaced.
1939 // We use dead_node as a placeholder for the original exception node before
1940 // it's uses are rewired.
1941
1942 Node* dead_node = jsgraph()->Dead();
1943 if_exception_merge =
1944 graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(5), dead_node, dead_node, dead_node,
1945 dead_node, dead_node);
1946 if_exception_effect_phi =
1947 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(5), dead_node, dead_node,
1948 dead_node, dead_node, dead_node, if_exception_merge);
1949 if_exception_phi = graph()->NewNode(
1950 common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 5), dead_node, dead_node,
1951 dead_node, dead_node, dead_node, if_exception_merge);
1952 // Rewire the original exception node uses.
1953 ReplaceWithValue(iterator_exception_node, if_exception_phi,
1954 if_exception_effect_phi, if_exception_merge);
1955 if_exception_merge->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index,
1956 iterator_exception_node);
1957 if_exception_effect_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index,
1958 iterator_exception_node);
1959 if_exception_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index,
1960 iterator_exception_node);
1961 exception_node_index++;
1962 }
1963
1964 // Load iterator property operator
1965 NameRef iterator_symbol = broker()->iterator_symbol();
1966 const Operator* load_op =
1967 javascript()->LoadNamed(iterator_symbol, p.loadFeedback());
1968
1969 // Lazy deopt of the load iterator property
1970 // TODO(v8:10047): Use TaggedIndexConstant here once deoptimizer supports it.
1971 Node* call_slot = jsgraph()->SmiConstant(p.callFeedback().slot.ToInt());
1972 Node* call_feedback = jsgraph()->HeapConstantNoHole(p.callFeedback().vector);
1973 Node* lazy_deopt_parameters[] = {receiver, call_slot, call_feedback};
1974 Node* lazy_deopt_frame_state = CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
1975 jsgraph(), Builtin::kGetIteratorWithFeedbackLazyDeoptContinuation,
1976 context, lazy_deopt_parameters, arraysize(lazy_deopt_parameters),
1977 frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
1978 Node* load_property =
1979 graph()->NewNode(load_op, receiver, n.feedback_vector(), context,
1980 lazy_deopt_frame_state, effect, control);
1981 effect = load_property;
1982 control = load_property;
1983
1984 // Merge the exception path for LoadNamed.
1985 if (has_exception_node) {
1986 Node* if_exception =
1987 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), effect, control);
1988 if_exception_merge->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
1989 if_exception_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
1990 if_exception_effect_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
1991 exception_node_index++;
1992 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control);
1993 }
1994
1995 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), load_property,
1996 jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
1997 Node* branch =
1998 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kFalse), check, control);
1999
2000 {
2001 Node* if_not_iterator = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
2002 Node* effect_not_iterator = effect;
2003 Node* control_not_iterator = if_not_iterator;
2004 Node* call_runtime = effect_not_iterator = control_not_iterator =
2005 graph()->NewNode(
2006 javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowIteratorError, 1),
2007 receiver, context, frame_state, effect_not_iterator,
2008 control_not_iterator);
2009 // Merge the exception path for CallRuntime.
2010 if (has_exception_node) {
2011 Node* if_exception = graph()->NewNode(
2012 common()->IfException(), effect_not_iterator, control_not_iterator);
2013 if_exception_merge->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2014 if_exception_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2015 if_exception_effect_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2016 exception_node_index++;
2017 control_not_iterator =
2018 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control_not_iterator);
2019 }
2020 Node* throw_node =
2021 graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), call_runtime, control_not_iterator);
2022 MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), throw_node);
2023 }
2024
2025 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
2026
2027 // Eager deopt of call iterator property
2028 Node* parameters[] = {receiver, load_property, call_slot, call_feedback};
2029 Node* eager_deopt_frame_state = CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
2030 jsgraph(), Builtin::kCallIteratorWithFeedback, context, parameters,
2031 arraysize(parameters), frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode::EAGER);
2032 Node* deopt_checkpoint = graph()->NewNode(
2033 common()->Checkpoint(), eager_deopt_frame_state, effect, control);
2034 effect = deopt_checkpoint;
2035
2036 // Call iterator property operator
2037 ProcessedFeedback const& feedback =
2038 broker()->GetFeedbackForCall(p.callFeedback());
2039 SpeculationMode mode = feedback.IsInsufficient()
2040 ? SpeculationMode::kDisallowSpeculation
2041 : feedback.AsCall().speculation_mode();
2042 const Operator* call_op = javascript()->Call(
2043 JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(0), CallFrequency(), p.callFeedback(),
2044 ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined, mode,
2045 CallFeedbackRelation::kTarget);
2046 // Lazy deopt to check the call result is JSReceiver.
2047 Node* call_lazy_deopt_frame_state = CreateStubBuiltinContinuationFrameState(
2048 jsgraph(), Builtin::kCallIteratorWithFeedbackLazyDeoptContinuation,
2049 context, nullptr, 0, frame_state, ContinuationFrameStateMode::LAZY);
2050 Node* call_property = effect = control =
2051 graph()->NewNode(call_op, load_property, receiver, n.feedback_vector(),
2052 context, call_lazy_deopt_frame_state, effect, control);
2053
2054 // Merge the exception path for Call.
2055 if (has_exception_node) {
2056 Node* if_exception =
2057 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), effect, control);
2058 if_exception_merge->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2059 if_exception_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2060 if_exception_effect_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2061 exception_node_index++;
2062 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control);
2063 }
2064
2065 // If the result is not JSReceiver, throw invalid iterator exception.
2066 Node* is_receiver =
2067 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsReceiver(), call_property);
2068 Node* branch_node = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue),
2069 is_receiver, control);
2070 {
2071 Node* if_not_receiver = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch_node);
2072 Node* effect_not_receiver = effect;
2073 Node* control_not_receiver = if_not_receiver;
2074 Node* call_runtime = effect_not_receiver = control_not_receiver =
2075 graph()->NewNode(
2076 javascript()->CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowSymbolIteratorInvalid, 0),
2077 context, frame_state, effect_not_receiver, control_not_receiver);
2078 // Merge the exception path for CallRuntime.
2079 if (has_exception_node) {
2080 Node* if_exception = graph()->NewNode(
2081 common()->IfException(), effect_not_receiver, control_not_receiver);
2082 if_exception_merge->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2083 if_exception_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2084 if_exception_effect_phi->ReplaceInput(exception_node_index, if_exception);
2085 exception_node_index++;
2086 control_not_receiver =
2087 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control_not_receiver);
2088 }
2089 Node* throw_node =
2090 graph()->NewNode(common()->Throw(), call_runtime, control_not_receiver);
2091 MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), throw_node);
2092 }
2093 Node* if_receiver = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch_node);
2094 ReplaceWithValue(node, call_property, effect, if_receiver);
2095
2096 if (has_exception_node) {
2097 DCHECK_EQ(exception_node_index, if_exception_merge->InputCount());
2098 DCHECK_EQ(exception_node_index, if_exception_effect_phi->InputCount() - 1);
2099 DCHECK_EQ(exception_node_index, if_exception_phi->InputCount() - 1);
2100#ifdef DEBUG
2101 for (Node* input : if_exception_merge->inputs()) {
2102 DCHECK(!input->IsDead());
2103 }
2104 for (Node* input : if_exception_effect_phi->inputs()) {
2105 DCHECK(!input->IsDead());
2106 }
2107 for (Node* input : if_exception_phi->inputs()) {
2108 DCHECK(!input->IsDead());
2109 }
2110#endif
2111 }
2112 return Replace(if_receiver);
2113}

2133Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceElementAccessOnString(
2134 Node* node, Node* index, Node* value, KeyedAccessMode const& keyed_mode) {
2135 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
2136 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
2137 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
2138
2139 // Strings are immutable in JavaScript.
2140 if (keyed_mode.access_mode() == AccessMode::kStore) return NoChange();
2141
2142 // `in` cannot be used on strings.
2143 if (keyed_mode.access_mode() == AccessMode::kHas) return NoChange();
2144
2145 // Ensure that the {receiver} is actually a String.
2146 receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2147 simplified()->CheckString(FeedbackSource()), receiver, effect, control);
2148
2149 // Determine the {receiver} length.
2150 Node* length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), receiver);
2151
2152 // Load the single character string from {receiver} or yield undefined
2153 // if the {index} is out of bounds (depending on the {load_mode}).
2154 value = BuildIndexedStringLoad(receiver, index, length, &effect, &control,
2155 keyed_mode.load_mode());
2156
2157 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
2158 return Replace(value);
2159}

2176void JSNativeContextSpecialization::RemoveImpossibleMaps(
2177 Node* object, ZoneVector<MapRef>* maps) const {
2178 OptionalMapRef root_map = InferRootMap(object);
2179 if (root_map.has_value() && !root_map->is_abandoned_prototype_map()) {
2180 maps->erase(
2181 std::remove_if(maps->begin(), maps->end(),
2182 [root_map, this](MapRef map) {
2183 return map.is_abandoned_prototype_map() ||
2184 !map.FindRootMap(broker()).equals(*root_map);
2185 }),
2186 maps->end());
2187 }

2190// Possibly refine the feedback using inferred map information from the graph.
2191ElementAccessFeedback const&
2192JSNativeContextSpecialization::TryRefineElementAccessFeedback(
2193 ElementAccessFeedback const& feedback, Node* receiver,
2194 Effect effect) const {
2195 AccessMode access_mode = feedback.keyed_mode().access_mode();
2196 bool use_inference =
2197 access_mode == AccessMode::kLoad || access_mode == AccessMode::kHas;
2198 if (!use_inference) return feedback;
2199
2200 ZoneVector<MapRef> inferred_maps(zone());
2201 if (!InferMaps(receiver, effect, &inferred_maps)) return feedback;
2202
2203 RemoveImpossibleMaps(receiver, &inferred_maps);
2204 // TODO(neis): After Refine, the resulting feedback can still contain
2205 // impossible maps when a target is kept only because more than one of its
2206 // sources was inferred. Think of a way to completely rule out impossible
2207 // maps.
2208 return feedback.Refine(broker(), inferred_maps);
2209}
2210
2211Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceElementAccess(
2212 Node* node, Node* index, Node* value,
2213 ElementAccessFeedback const& feedback) {
2214 DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadProperty ||
2215 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSSetKeyedProperty ||
2216 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSStoreInArrayLiteral ||
2217 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral ||
2218 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSHasProperty ||
2219 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnProperty);
2220 static_assert(JSLoadPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
2221 JSSetKeyedPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
2222 JSStoreInArrayLiteralNode::ArrayIndex() == 0 &&
2223 JSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteralNode::ObjectIndex() == 0 &&
2224 JSHasPropertyNode::ObjectIndex() == 0);
2225
2226 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
2227 Effect effect{NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node)};
2228 Control control{NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node)};
2229 Node* context = NodeProperties::GetContextInput(node);
2230
2231 // TODO(neis): It's odd that we do optimizations below that don't really care
2232 // about the feedback, but we don't do them when the feedback is megamorphic.
2233 if (feedback.transition_groups().empty()) return NoChange();
2234
2235 ElementAccessFeedback const& refined_feedback =
2236 TryRefineElementAccessFeedback(feedback, receiver, effect);
2237
2238 AccessMode access_mode = refined_feedback.keyed_mode().access_mode();
2239 if ((access_mode == AccessMode::kLoad || access_mode == AccessMode::kHas) &&
2240 receiver->opcode() == IrOpcode::kHeapConstant) {
2241 Reduction reduction = ReduceElementLoadFromHeapConstant(
2242 node, index, access_mode, refined_feedback.keyed_mode().load_mode());
2243 if (reduction.Changed()) return reduction;
2244 }
2245
2246 if (!refined_feedback.transition_groups().empty() &&
2247 refined_feedback.HasOnlyStringMaps(broker())) {
2248 return ReduceElementAccessOnString(node, index, value,
2249 refined_feedback.keyed_mode());
2250 }
2251
2252 AccessInfoFactory access_info_factory(broker(), graph()->zone());
2253 ZoneVector<ElementAccessInfo> access_infos(zone());
2254 if (!access_info_factory.ComputeElementAccessInfos(refined_feedback,
2255 &access_infos) ||
2256 access_infos.empty()) {
2257 return NoChange();
2258 }
2259
2260 // Do not optimize AccessMode::kDefine for typed arrays.
2261 if (access_mode == AccessMode::kDefine) {
2262 for (const ElementAccessInfo& access_info : access_infos) {
2263 if (IsTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(
2264 access_info.elements_kind())) {
2265 return NoChange();
2266 }
2267 }
2268 }
2269
2270 // Do not optimize Float16 typed arrays, since they are not yet supported by
2271 // the rest of the compiler.
2272 // TODO(v8:14012): We could lower further here and emit LoadTypedElement (like
2273 // we do for other typed arrays). However, given the lack of hardware support
2274 // for Float16 operations, it's not clear whether optimizing further would be
2275 // really useful.
2276 for (const ElementAccessInfo& access_info : access_infos) {
2277 if (IsFloat16TypedArrayElementsKind(access_info.elements_kind())) {
2278 return NoChange();
2279 }
2280 }
2281
2282 // For holey stores or growing stores, we need to check that the prototype
2283 // chain contains no setters for elements, and we need to guard those checks
2284 // via code dependencies on the relevant prototype maps.
2285 if (access_mode == AccessMode::kStore) {
2286 // TODO(turbofan): We could have a fast path here, that checks for the
2287 // common case of Array or Object prototype only and therefore avoids
2288 // the zone allocation of this vector.
2289 ZoneVector<MapRef> prototype_maps(zone());
2290 for (ElementAccessInfo const& access_info : access_infos) {
2291 for (MapRef receiver_map : access_info.lookup_start_object_maps()) {
2292 // If the {receiver_map} has a prototype and its elements backing
2293 // store is either holey, or we have a potentially growing store,
2294 // then we need to check that all prototypes have stable maps with
2295 // no element accessors and no throwing behavior for elements (and we
2296 // need to guard against changes to that below).
2297 if ((IsHoleyOrDictionaryElementsKind(receiver_map.elements_kind()) ||
2298 StoreModeCanGrow(feedback.keyed_mode().store_mode())) &&
2299 !receiver_map.PrototypesElementsDoNotHaveAccessorsOrThrow(
2300 broker(), &prototype_maps)) {
2301 return NoChange();
2302 }
2303
2304 // TODO(v8:12547): Support writing to objects in shared space, which
2305 // need a write barrier that calls Object::Share to ensure the RHS is
2306 // shared.
2307 if (InstanceTypeChecker::IsAlwaysSharedSpaceJSObject(
2308 receiver_map.instance_type())) {
2309 return NoChange();
2310 }
2311 }
2312 }
2313 for (MapRef prototype_map : prototype_maps) {
2314 dependencies()->DependOnStableMap(prototype_map);
2315 }
2316 } else if (access_mode == AccessMode::kHas) {
2317 // If we have any fast arrays, we need to check and depend on
2318 // NoElementsProtector.
2319 for (ElementAccessInfo const& access_info : access_infos) {
2320 if (IsFastElementsKind(access_info.elements_kind())) {
2321 if (!dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) return NoChange();
2322 break;
2323 }
2324 }
2325 }
2326
2327 // Check for the monomorphic case.
2328 PropertyAccessBuilder access_builder(jsgraph(), broker());
2329 if (access_infos.size() == 1) {
2330 ElementAccessInfo access_info = access_infos.front();
2331
2332 if (!access_info.transition_sources().empty()) {
2333 DCHECK_EQ(access_info.lookup_start_object_maps().size(), 1);
2334 // Perform possible elements kind transitions.
2335 MapRef transition_target = access_info.lookup_start_object_maps().front();
2336 ZoneRefSet<Map> sources(access_info.transition_sources().begin(),
2337 access_info.transition_sources().end(),
2338 graph()->zone());
2339 effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->TransitionElementsKindOrCheckMap(
2340 ElementsTransitionWithMultipleSources(
2341 sources, transition_target)),
2342 receiver, effect, control);
2343 } else {
2344 // Perform map check on the {receiver}.
2345 access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(receiver, &effect, control,
2346 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps());
2347 }
2348
2349 // Access the actual element.
2350 ValueEffectControl continuation =
2351 BuildElementAccess(receiver, index, value, effect, control, context,
2352 access_info, feedback.keyed_mode());
2353 value = continuation.value();
2354 effect = continuation.effect();
2355 control = continuation.control();
2356 } else {
2357 // The final states for every polymorphic branch. We join them with
2358 // Merge+Phi+EffectPhi at the bottom.
2359 ZoneVector<Node*> values(zone());
2360 ZoneVector<Node*> effects(zone());
2361 ZoneVector<Node*> controls(zone());
2362
2363 // Generate code for the various different element access patterns.
2364 Node* fallthrough_control = control;
2365 for (size_t j = 0; j < access_infos.size(); ++j) {
2366 ElementAccessInfo const& access_info = access_infos[j];
2367 Node* this_receiver = receiver;
2368 Node* this_value = value;
2369 Node* this_index = index;
2370 Effect this_effect = effect;
2371 Control this_control{fallthrough_control};
2372
2373 // Perform possible elements kind transitions.
2374 MapRef transition_target = access_info.lookup_start_object_maps().front();
2375 for (MapRef transition_source : access_info.transition_sources()) {
2376 DCHECK_EQ(access_info.lookup_start_object_maps().size(), 1);
2377 this_effect = graph()->NewNode(
2378 simplified()->TransitionElementsKind(ElementsTransition(
2379 IsSimpleMapChangeTransition(transition_source.elements_kind(),
2380 transition_target.elements_kind())
2381 ? ElementsTransition::kFastTransition
2382 : ElementsTransition::kSlowTransition,
2383 transition_source, transition_target)),
2384 receiver, this_effect, this_control);
2385 }
2386
2387 // Perform map check(s) on {receiver}.
2388 ZoneVector<MapRef> const& receiver_maps =
2389 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps();
2390 if (j == access_infos.size() - 1) {
2391 // Last map check on the fallthrough control path, do a
2392 // conditional eager deoptimization exit here.
2393 access_builder.BuildCheckMaps(receiver, &this_effect, this_control,
2394 receiver_maps);
2395 fallthrough_control = nullptr;
2396 } else {
2397 // Explicitly branch on the {receiver_maps}.
2398 ZoneRefSet<Map> maps(receiver_maps.begin(), receiver_maps.end(),
2399 graph()->zone());
2400 Node* check = this_effect =
2401 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CompareMaps(maps), receiver,
2402 this_effect, fallthrough_control);
2403 Node* branch =
2404 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, fallthrough_control);
2405 fallthrough_control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
2406 this_control = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
2407
2408 // Introduce a MapGuard to learn from this on the effect chain.
2409 this_effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->MapGuard(maps), receiver,
2410 this_effect, this_control);
2411 }
2412
2413 // Access the actual element.
2414 ValueEffectControl continuation = BuildElementAccess(
2415 this_receiver, this_index, this_value, this_effect, this_control,
2416 context, access_info, feedback.keyed_mode());
2417 values.push_back(continuation.value());
2418 effects.push_back(continuation.effect());
2419 controls.push_back(continuation.control());
2420 }
2421
2422 DCHECK_NULL(fallthrough_control);
2423
2424 // Generate the final merge point for all (polymorphic) branches.
2425 int const control_count = static_cast<int>(controls.size());
2426 if (control_count == 0) {
2427 value = effect = control = jsgraph()->Dead();
2428 } else if (control_count == 1) {
2429 value = values.front();
2430 effect = effects.front();
2431 control = controls.front();
2432 } else {
2433 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(control_count), control_count,
2434 &controls.front());
2435 values.push_back(control);
2436 value = graph()->NewNode(
2437 common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, control_count),
2438 control_count + 1, &values.front());
2439 effects.push_back(control);
2440 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(control_count),
2441 control_count + 1, &effects.front());
2442 }
2443 }
2444
2445 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
2446 return Replace(value);
2447}
2448
2449Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceElementLoadFromHeapConstant(
2450 Node* node, Node* key, AccessMode access_mode,
2451 KeyedAccessLoadMode load_mode) {
2452 DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadProperty ||
2453 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSHasProperty);
2454 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
2455 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
2456 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
2457
2458 HeapObjectMatcher mreceiver(receiver);
2459 HeapObjectRef receiver_ref = mreceiver.Ref(broker());
2460 if (receiver_ref.IsNull() || receiver_ref.IsUndefined() ||
2461 // The 'in' operator throws a TypeError on primitive values.
2462 (receiver_ref.IsString() && access_mode == AccessMode::kHas)) {
2463 return NoChange();
2464 }
2465
2466 // Check whether we're accessing a known element on the {receiver} and can
2467 // constant-fold the load.
2468 NumberMatcher mkey(key);
2469 if (mkey.IsInteger() &&
2470 mkey.IsInRange(0.0, static_cast<double>(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex))) {
2471 static_assert(JSObject::kMaxElementIndex <= kMaxUInt32);
2472 const uint32_t index = static_cast<uint32_t>(mkey.ResolvedValue());
2473 OptionalObjectRef element;
2474
2475 if (receiver_ref.IsJSObject()) {
2476 JSObjectRef jsobject_ref = receiver_ref.AsJSObject();
2477 OptionalFixedArrayBaseRef elements =
2478 jsobject_ref.elements(broker(), kRelaxedLoad);
2479 if (elements.has_value()) {
2480 element = jsobject_ref.GetOwnConstantElement(broker(), *elements, index,
2481 dependencies());
2482 if (!element.has_value() && receiver_ref.IsJSArray()) {
2483 // We didn't find a constant element, but if the receiver is a
2484 // cow-array we can exploit the fact that any future write to the
2485 // element will replace the whole elements storage.
2486 element = receiver_ref.AsJSArray().GetOwnCowElement(broker(),
2487 *elements, index);
2488 if (element.has_value()) {
2489 Node* actual_elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2490 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()),
2491 receiver, effect, control);
2492 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(
2493 simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), actual_elements,
2494 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(*elements, broker()));
2495 effect = graph()->NewNode(
2496 simplified()->CheckIf(
2497 DeoptimizeReason::kCowArrayElementsChanged),
2498 check, effect, control);
2499 }
2500 }
2501 }
2502 } else if (receiver_ref.IsString()) {
2503 element =
2504 receiver_ref.AsString().GetCharAsStringOrUndefined(broker(), index);
2505 }
2506
2507 if (element.has_value()) {
2508 Node* value = access_mode == AccessMode::kHas
2509 ? jsgraph()->TrueConstant()
2510 : jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(*element, broker());
2511 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
2512 return Replace(value);
2513 }
2514 }
2515
2516 // For constant Strings we can eagerly strength-reduce the keyed
2517 // accesses using the known length, which doesn't change.
2518 if (receiver_ref.IsString()) {
2519 DCHECK_NE(access_mode, AccessMode::kHas);
2520 // Ensure that {key} is less than {receiver} length.
2521 Node* length = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(receiver_ref.AsString().length());
2522
2523 // Load the single character string from {receiver} or yield
2524 // undefined if the {key} is out of bounds (depending on the
2525 // {load_mode}).
2526 Node* value = BuildIndexedStringLoad(receiver, key, length, &effect,
2527 &control, load_mode);
2528 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
2529 return Replace(value);
2530 }
2531
2532 return NoChange();
2533}
2534
2535Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReducePropertyAccess(
2536 Node* node, Node* key, OptionalNameRef static_name, Node* value,
2537 FeedbackSource const& source, AccessMode access_mode) {
2538 DCHECK_EQ(key == nullptr, static_name.has_value());
2539 DCHECK(node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadProperty ||
2540 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSSetKeyedProperty ||
2541 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSStoreInArrayLiteral ||
2542 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnPropertyInLiteral ||
2543 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSHasProperty ||
2544 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamed ||
2545 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSSetNamedProperty ||
2546 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineNamedOwnProperty ||
2547 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamedFromSuper ||
2548 node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSDefineKeyedOwnProperty);
2549 DCHECK_GE(node->op()->ControlOutputCount(), 1);
2550
2551 ProcessedFeedback const* feedback =
2552 &broker()->GetFeedbackForPropertyAccess(source, access_mode, static_name);
2553
2554 if (feedback->kind() == ProcessedFeedback::kElementAccess &&
2555 feedback->AsElementAccess().transition_groups().empty()) {
2556 HeapObjectMatcher m_key(key);
2557 if (m_key.HasResolvedValue() && m_key.Ref(broker()).IsName()) {
2558 NameRef name_key = m_key.Ref(broker()).AsName();
2559 if (name_key.IsUniqueName() && !name_key.object()->IsArrayIndex()) {
2560 feedback = &feedback->AsElementAccess().Refine(
2561 broker(), m_key.Ref(broker()).AsName());
2562 }
2563 }
2564 }
2565
2566 switch (feedback->kind()) {
2567 case ProcessedFeedback::kInsufficient:
2568 return ReduceEagerDeoptimize(
2569 node,
2570 DeoptimizeReason::kInsufficientTypeFeedbackForGenericNamedAccess);
2571 case ProcessedFeedback::kNamedAccess:
2572 return ReduceNamedAccess(node, value, feedback->AsNamedAccess(),
2573 access_mode, key);
2574 case ProcessedFeedback::kMegaDOMPropertyAccess:
2575 DCHECK_EQ(access_mode, AccessMode::kLoad);
2576 DCHECK_NULL(key);
2577 return ReduceMegaDOMPropertyAccess(
2578 node, value, feedback->AsMegaDOMPropertyAccess(), source);
2579 case ProcessedFeedback::kElementAccess:
2580 DCHECK_EQ(feedback->AsElementAccess().keyed_mode().access_mode(),
2581 access_mode);
2582 DCHECK_NE(node->opcode(), IrOpcode::kJSLoadNamedFromSuper);
2583 return ReduceElementAccess(node, key, value, feedback->AsElementAccess());
2584 default:
2585 UNREACHABLE();
2586 }
2587}
2588
2589Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceEagerDeoptimize(
2590 Node* node, DeoptimizeReason reason) {
2591 if (!(flags() & kBailoutOnUninitialized)) return NoChange();
2592
2593 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
2594 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
2595 Node* frame_state =
2596 NodeProperties::FindFrameStateBefore(node, jsgraph()->Dead());
2597 Node* deoptimize =
2598 graph()->NewNode(common()->Deoptimize(reason, FeedbackSource()),
2599 frame_state, effect, control);
2600 MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), deoptimize);
2601 node->TrimInputCount(0);
2602 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, common()->Dead());
2603 return Changed(node);
2604}

2606Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSHasProperty(Node* node) {
2607 JSHasPropertyNode n(node);
2608 PropertyAccess const& p = n.Parameters();
2609 Node* value = jsgraph()->Dead();
2610 if (!p.feedback().IsValid()) return NoChange();
2611 return ReducePropertyAccess(node, n.key(), std::nullopt, value,
2612 FeedbackSource(p.feedback()), AccessMode::kHas);

2614
2615Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSLoadPropertyWithEnumeratedKey(
2616 Node* node) {
2617 // We can optimize a property load if it's being used inside a for..in:
2618 // for (name in receiver) {
2619 // value = receiver[name];
2620 // ...
2621 // }
2622 //
2623 // If the for..in is in fast-mode, we know that the {receiver} has {name}
2624 // as own property, otherwise the enumeration wouldn't include it. The graph
2625 // constructed by the BytecodeGraphBuilder in this case looks like this:
2626
2627 // receiver
2628 // ^ ^
2629 // | |
2630 // | +-+
2631 // | |
2632 // | JSToObject
2633 // | ^
2634 // | |
2635 // | |
2636 // | JSForInNext
2637 // | ^
2638 // | |
2639 // +----+ |
2640 // | |
2641 // | |
2642 // JSLoadProperty
2643
2644 // If the for..in has only seen maps with enum cache consisting of keys
2645 // and indices so far, we can turn the {JSLoadProperty} into a map check
2646 // on the {receiver} and then just load the field value dynamically via
2647 // the {LoadFieldByIndex} operator. The map check is only necessary when
2648 // TurboFan cannot prove that there is no observable side effect between
2649 // the {JSForInNext} and the {JSLoadProperty} node.
2650 //
2651 // We can do a similar optimization when the receiver of {JSLoadProperty} is
2652 // not identical to the receiver of {JSForInNext}:
2653 // for (name in receiver) {
2654 // value = object[name];
2655 // ...
2656 // }
2657 //
2658 // This is because when the key is {JSForInNext}, we will generate a
2659 // {GetEnumeratedKeyedProperty} bytecode for {JSLoadProperty}. If the bytecode
2660 // always manages to use the enum cache, we will keep the inline cache in
2661 // uninitialized state. So If the graph is as below, we can firstly do a map
2662 // check on {object} and then turn the {JSLoadProperty} into the
2663 // {LoadFieldByIndex}. This is also safe when the bytecode has never been
2664 // profiled. When it happens to pass the the map check, we can use the fast
2665 // path. Otherwise it will trigger a deoptimization.
2666
2667 // object receiver
2668 // ^ ^
2669 // | |
2670 // | |
2671 // | |
2672 // | JSToObject
2673 // | ^
2674 // | |
2675 // | |
2676 // | JSForInNext
2677 // | ^
2678 // | |
2679 // +----+ +-----+
2680 // | |
2681 // | |
2682 // JSLoadProperty (insufficient feedback)
2683
2684 // Also note that it's safe to look through the {JSToObject}, since the
2685 // [[Get]] operation does an implicit ToObject anyway, and these operations
2686 // are not observable.
2687
2688 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kJSLoadProperty, node->opcode());
2689 Node* receiver = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 0);
2690 JSForInNextNode name(NodeProperties::GetValueInput(node, 1));
2691 Node* effect = NodeProperties::GetEffectInput(node);
2692 Node* control = NodeProperties::GetControlInput(node);
2693
2694 if (name.Parameters().mode() != ForInMode::kUseEnumCacheKeysAndIndices) {
2695 return NoChange();
2696 }
2697
2698 Node* object = name.receiver();
2699 Node* cache_type = name.cache_type();
2700 Node* index = name.index();
2701 if (object->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSToObject) {
2702 object = NodeProperties::GetValueInput(object, 0);
2703 }
2704 bool speculating_object_is_receiver = false;
2705 if (object != receiver) {
2706 JSLoadPropertyNode n(node);
2707 PropertyAccess const& p = n.Parameters();
2708
2709 ProcessedFeedback const& feedback = broker()->GetFeedbackForPropertyAccess(
2710 FeedbackSource(p.feedback()), AccessMode::kLoad, std::nullopt);
2711 // When the feedback is uninitialized, it is either a load from a
2712 // {GetEnumeratedKeyedProperty} which always hits the enum cache, or a keyed
2713 // load that had never been reached. In either case, we can check the map
2714 // of the receiver and use the enum cache if the map match the {cache_type}.
2715 if (feedback.kind() != ProcessedFeedback::kInsufficient) {
2716 return NoChange();
2717 }
2718
2719 // Ensure that {receiver} is a HeapObject.
2720 receiver = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckHeapObject(),
2721 receiver, effect, control);
2722 speculating_object_is_receiver = true;
2723 }
2724
2725 // No need to repeat the map check if we can prove that there's no
2726 // observable side effect between {effect} and {name]. But we always need a
2727 // map check when {object} is not identical to {receiver}.
2728 if (!NodeProperties::NoObservableSideEffectBetween(effect, name) ||
2729 speculating_object_is_receiver) {
2730 // Check that the {receiver} map is still valid.
2731 Node* receiver_map = effect =
2732 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()),
2733 receiver, effect, control);
2734 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), receiver_map,
2735 cache_type);
2736 effect =
2737 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap),
2738 check, effect, control);
2739 }
2740
2741 // Load the enum cache indices from the {cache_type}.
2742 Node* descriptor_array = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2743 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapDescriptors()), cache_type,
2744 effect, control);
2745 Node* enum_cache = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2746 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForDescriptorArrayEnumCache()),
2747 descriptor_array, effect, control);
2748 Node* enum_indices = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2749 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForEnumCacheIndices()), enum_cache,
2750 effect, control);
2751
2752 // Ensure that the {enum_indices} are valid.
2753 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(
2754 simplified()->BooleanNot(),
2755 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), enum_indices,
2756 jsgraph()->EmptyFixedArrayConstant()));
2757 effect = graph()->NewNode(
2758 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kWrongEnumIndices), check, effect,
2759 control);
2760
2761 // Determine the key from the {enum_indices}.
2762 Node* key = effect = graph()->NewNode(
2763 simplified()->LoadElement(
2764 AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayElement(PACKED_SMI_ELEMENTS)),
2765 enum_indices, index, effect, control);
2766
2767 // Load the actual field value.
2768 Node* value = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadFieldByIndex(),
2769 receiver, key, effect, control);
2770 ReplaceWithValue(node, value, effect, control);
2771 return Replace(value);
2772}
2773
2774Reduction JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReduceJSLoadProperty(Node* node) {
2775 JSLoadPropertyNode n(node);
2776 PropertyAccess const& p = n.Parameters();
2777 Node* name = n.key();
2778
2779 if (name->opcode() == IrOpcode::kJSForInNext) {
2780 Reduction reduction = ReduceJSLoadPropertyWithEnumeratedKey(node);
2781 if (reduction.Changed()) return reduction;
2782 }
2783
2784 if (!p.feedback().IsValid()) return NoChange();
2785 Node* value = jsgraph()->Dead();
2786 return ReducePropertyAccess(node, name, std::nullopt, value,
2787 FeedbackSource(p.feedback()), AccessMode::kLoad);
2788}

2807
2808Node* JSNativeContextSpecialization::InlinePropertyGetterCall(
2809 Node* receiver, ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode,
2810 Node* lookup_start_object, Node* context, Node* frame_state, Node** effect,
2811 Node** control, ZoneVector<Node*>* if_exceptions,
2812 PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info) {
2813 ObjectRef constant = access_info.constant().value();
2814
2815 if (access_info.IsDictionaryProtoAccessorConstant()) {
2816 // For fast mode holders we recorded dependencies in BuildPropertyLoad.
2817 for (const MapRef map : access_info.lookup_start_object_maps()) {
2818 dependencies()->DependOnConstantInDictionaryPrototypeChain(
2819 map, access_info.name(), constant, PropertyKind::kAccessor);
2820 }
2821 }
2822
2823 Node* target = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(constant, broker());
2824 // Introduce the call to the getter function.
2825 Node* value;
2826 if (constant.IsJSFunction()) {
2827 Node* feedback = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
2828 value = *effect = *control = graph()->NewNode(
2829 jsgraph()->javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(0),
2830 CallFrequency(), FeedbackSource(),
2831 receiver_mode),
2832 target, receiver, feedback, context, frame_state, *effect, *control);
2833 } else {
2834 // Disable optimizations for super ICs using API getters, so that we get
2835 // the correct receiver checks.
2836 if (receiver != lookup_start_object) {
2837 return nullptr;
2838 }
2839 Node* api_holder = access_info.api_holder().has_value()
2840 ? jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
2841 access_info.api_holder().value(), broker())
2842 : receiver;
2843 value = InlineApiCall(receiver, api_holder, frame_state, nullptr, effect,
2844 control, constant.AsFunctionTemplateInfo(),
2845 FeedbackSource());
2846 }
2847 // Remember to rewire the IfException edge if this is inside a try-block.
2848 if (if_exceptions != nullptr) {
2849 // Create the appropriate IfException/IfSuccess projections.
2850 Node* const if_exception =
2851 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), *control, *effect);
2852 Node* const if_success = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), *control);
2853 if_exceptions->push_back(if_exception);
2854 *control = if_success;
2855 }
2856 return value;
2857}

2859void JSNativeContextSpecialization::InlinePropertySetterCall(
2860 Node* receiver, Node* value, Node* context, Node* frame_state,
2861 Node** effect, Node** control, ZoneVector<Node*>* if_exceptions,
2862 PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info) {
2863 ObjectRef constant = access_info.constant().value();
2864 Node* target = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(constant, broker());
2865 // Introduce the call to the setter function.
2866 if (constant.IsJSFunction()) {
2867 Node* feedback = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
2868 *effect = *control = graph()->NewNode(
2869 jsgraph()->javascript()->Call(JSCallNode::ArityForArgc(1),
2870 CallFrequency(), FeedbackSource(),
2871 ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined),
2872 target, receiver, value, feedback, context, frame_state, *effect,
2873 *control);
2874 } else {
2875 Node* api_holder = access_info.api_holder().has_value()
2876 ? jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
2877 access_info.api_holder().value(), broker())
2878 : receiver;
2879 InlineApiCall(receiver, api_holder, frame_state, value, effect, control,
2880 constant.AsFunctionTemplateInfo(), FeedbackSource());
2881 }
2882 // Remember to rewire the IfException edge if this is inside a try-block.
2883 if (if_exceptions != nullptr) {
2884 // Create the appropriate IfException/IfSuccess projections.
2885 Node* const if_exception =
2886 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), *control, *effect);
2887 Node* const if_success = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), *control);
2888 if_exceptions->push_back(if_exception);
2889 *control = if_success;
2890 }
2891}

2893namespace {
2894CallDescriptor* PushRegularApiCallInputs(
2895 JSGraph* jsgraph, JSHeapBroker* broker, Node* receiver, Node* api_holder,
2896 Node* frame_state, Node* value, Node** effect, Node** control,
2897 FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info, Node** inputs,
2898 int& cursor) {
2899 // Only setters have a value.
2900 int const argc = value == nullptr ? 0 : 1;
2901
2902 // The builtin always expects the receiver as the first param on the stack.
2903 bool no_profiling = broker->dependencies()->DependOnNoProfilingProtector();
2904 Callable call_api_callback = Builtins::CallableFor(
2905 jsgraph->isolate(), no_profiling
2906 ? Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimizedNoProfiling
2907 : Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimized);
2908
2909 Node* func_templ =
2910 jsgraph->HeapConstantNoHole(function_template_info.object());
2911 ApiFunction function(function_template_info.callback(broker));
2912 Node* function_reference = jsgraph->graph()->NewNode(
2913 jsgraph->common()->ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(
2914 jsgraph->isolate(), &function, ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL,
2915 function_template_info.c_functions(broker).data(),
2916 function_template_info.c_signatures(broker).data(),
2917 static_cast<uint32_t>(
2918 function_template_info.c_functions(broker).size()))));
2919 Node* code = jsgraph->HeapConstantNoHole(call_api_callback.code());
2920
2921 // Add CallApiCallbackStub's register argument as well.
2922 Node* context =
2923 jsgraph->ConstantNoHole(broker->target_native_context(), broker);
2924 inputs[cursor++] = code;
2925 inputs[cursor++] = function_reference;
2926 inputs[cursor++] = jsgraph->ConstantNoHole(argc);
2927 inputs[cursor++] = func_templ;
2928 inputs[cursor++] = api_holder;
2929 inputs[cursor++] = receiver;
2930 if (value) {
2931 inputs[cursor++] = value;
2932 }
2933 inputs[cursor++] = context;
2934 inputs[cursor++] = frame_state;
2935 inputs[cursor++] = *effect;
2936 inputs[cursor++] = *control;
2937
2938 CallInterfaceDescriptor call_interface_descriptor =
2939 call_api_callback.descriptor();
2940 return Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
2941 jsgraph->zone(), call_interface_descriptor,
2942 call_interface_descriptor.GetStackParameterCount() + argc +
2943 1 /* implicit receiver */,
2944 CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState);
2945}

2947
2948Node* JSNativeContextSpecialization::InlineApiCall(
2949 Node* receiver, Node* api_holder, Node* frame_state, Node* value,
2950 Node** effect, Node** control,
2951 FunctionTemplateInfoRef function_template_info,
2952 const FeedbackSource& feedback) {
2953 compiler::OptionalObjectRef maybe_callback_data =
2954 function_template_info.callback_data(broker());
2955 // Check if the function has an associated C++ code to execute.
2956 if (!maybe_callback_data.has_value()) {
2957 // TODO(ishell): consider generating "return undefined" for empty function
2958 // instead of failing.
2959 TRACE_BROKER_MISSING(broker(), "call code for function template info "
2960 << function_template_info);
2961 return nullptr;
2962 }
2963
2964 // Only setters have a value.
2965 int const argc = value == nullptr ? 0 : 1;
2966
2967 // Handles overloaded functions.
2968 FastApiCallFunction c_function = fast_api_call::GetFastApiCallTarget(
2969 broker(), function_template_info, argc);
2970
2971 if (c_function.address) {
2972 const int input_count = 14;
2973 Node* inputs[input_count];
2974
2975 int cursor = 0;
2976 inputs[cursor++] = receiver;
2977 if (value) {
2978 inputs[cursor++] = value;
2979 }
2980 inputs[cursor++] =
2981 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(maybe_callback_data.value(), broker());
2982
2983 auto call_descriptor = PushRegularApiCallInputs(
2984 jsgraph(), broker(), receiver, api_holder, frame_state, value, effect,
2985 control, function_template_info, inputs, cursor);
2986
2987 // The input_count is constant, but getters have less parameters than
2988 // setters.
2989 DCHECK_LE(cursor, input_count);
2990
2991 return *effect = *control = graph()->NewNode(
2992 simplified()->FastApiCall(c_function, feedback, call_descriptor),
2993 cursor, inputs);
2994 }
2995
2996 Node* inputs[11];
2997 int cursor = 0;
2998 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = PushRegularApiCallInputs(
2999 jsgraph(), broker(), receiver, api_holder, frame_state, value, effect,
3000 control, function_template_info, inputs, cursor);
3001
3002 return *effect = *control =
3003 graph()->NewNode(common()->Call(call_descriptor), cursor, inputs);
3004}

3006std::optional<JSNativeContextSpecialization::ValueEffectControl>
3007JSNativeContextSpecialization::BuildPropertyLoad(
3008 Node* lookup_start_object, Node* receiver, Node* context, Node* frame_state,
3009 Node* effect, Node* control, NameRef name, ZoneVector<Node*>* if_exceptions,
3010 PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info) {
3011 // Determine actual holder and perform prototype chain checks.
3012 OptionalJSObjectRef holder = access_info.holder();
3013 if (holder.has_value() && !access_info.HasDictionaryHolder()) {
3014 dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
3015 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), kStartAtPrototype,
3016 holder.value());
3017 }
3018
3019 // Generate the actual property access.
3020 Node* value;
3021 if (access_info.IsNotFound()) {
3022 value = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
3023 } else if (access_info.IsFastAccessorConstant() ||
3024 access_info.IsDictionaryProtoAccessorConstant()) {
3025 ConvertReceiverMode receiver_mode =
3026 receiver == lookup_start_object
3027 ? ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined
3028 : ConvertReceiverMode::kAny;
3029 value = InlinePropertyGetterCall(
3030 receiver, receiver_mode, lookup_start_object, context, frame_state,
3031 &effect, &control, if_exceptions, access_info);
3032 } else if (access_info.IsModuleExport()) {
3033 Node* cell = jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(
3034 access_info.constant().value().AsCell(), broker());
3035 value = effect =
3036 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForCellValue()),
3037 cell, effect, control);
3038 } else if (access_info.IsStringLength()) {
3039 DCHECK_EQ(receiver, lookup_start_object);
3040 value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringLength(), receiver);
3041 } else if (access_info.IsStringWrapperLength()) {
3042 value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringWrapperLength(),
3043 lookup_start_object);
3044 } else {
3045 DCHECK(access_info.IsDataField() || access_info.IsFastDataConstant() ||
3046 access_info.IsDictionaryProtoDataConstant());
3047 PropertyAccessBuilder access_builder(jsgraph(), broker());
3048 if (access_info.IsDictionaryProtoDataConstant()) {
3049 auto maybe_value =
3050 access_builder.FoldLoadDictPrototypeConstant(access_info);
3051 if (!maybe_value) return {};
3052 value = maybe_value.value();
3053 } else {
3054 value = access_builder.BuildLoadDataField(
3055 name, access_info, lookup_start_object, &effect, &control);
3056 }
3057 }
3058 if (value != nullptr) {
3059 return ValueEffectControl(value, effect, control);
3060 }
3061 return std::optional<ValueEffectControl>();
3062}

3083JSNativeContextSpecialization::BuildPropertyAccess(

3106
3107JSNativeContextSpecialization::ValueEffectControl
3108JSNativeContextSpecialization::BuildPropertyStore(
3109 Node* receiver, Node* value, Node* context, Node* frame_state, Node* effect,
3110 Node* control, NameRef name, ZoneVector<Node*>* if_exceptions,
3111 PropertyAccessInfo const& access_info, AccessMode access_mode) {
3112 // Determine actual holder and perform prototype chain checks.
3113 PropertyAccessBuilder access_builder(jsgraph(), broker());
3114 OptionalJSObjectRef holder = access_info.holder();
3115 if (holder.has_value()) {
3116 DCHECK_NE(AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral, access_mode);
3117 DCHECK_NE(AccessMode::kDefine, access_mode);
3118 dependencies()->DependOnStablePrototypeChains(
3119 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps(), kStartAtPrototype,
3120 holder.value());
3121 }
3122
3123 DCHECK(!access_info.IsNotFound());
3124
3125 // Generate the actual property access.
3126 if (access_info.IsFastAccessorConstant()) {
3127 InlinePropertySetterCall(receiver, value, context, frame_state, &effect,
3128 &control, if_exceptions, access_info);
3129 } else {
3130 DCHECK(access_info.IsDataField() || access_info.IsFastDataConstant());
3131 DCHECK(access_mode == AccessMode::kStore ||
3132 access_mode == AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral ||
3133 access_mode == AccessMode::kDefine);
3134 FieldIndex const field_index = access_info.field_index();
3135 Type const field_type = access_info.field_type();
3136 MachineRepresentation const field_representation =
3137 PropertyAccessBuilder::ConvertRepresentation(
3138 access_info.field_representation());
3139 Node* storage = receiver;
3140 if (!field_index.is_inobject()) {
3141 storage = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3142 simplified()->LoadField(
3143 AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectPropertiesOrHashKnownPointer()),
3144 storage, effect, control);
3145 }
3146 if (access_info.IsFastDataConstant() && access_mode == AccessMode::kStore &&
3147 !access_info.HasTransitionMap()) {
3148 Node* deoptimize = graph()->NewNode(
3149 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kStoreToConstant),
3150 jsgraph()->FalseConstant(), effect, control);
3151 return ValueEffectControl(jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant(), deoptimize,
3152 control);
3153 }
3154 FieldAccess field_access = {
3155 kTaggedBase,
3156 field_index.offset(),
3157 name.object(),
3158 OptionalMapRef(),
3159 field_type,
3160 MachineType::TypeForRepresentation(field_representation),
3161 kFullWriteBarrier,
3162 "BuildPropertyStore",
3163 access_info.GetConstFieldInfo(),
3164 access_mode == AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral};
3165
3166 switch (field_representation) {
3167 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat64: {
3168 value = effect =
3169 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckNumber(FeedbackSource()), value,
3170 effect, control);
3171 if (access_info.HasTransitionMap()) {
3172 // Allocate a HeapNumber for the new property.
3173 AllocationBuilder a(jsgraph(), broker(), effect, control);
3174 a.Allocate(sizeof(HeapNumber), AllocationType::kYoung,
3175 Type::OtherInternal());
3176 a.Store(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), broker()->heap_number_map());
3177 FieldAccess value_field_access = AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue();
3178 value_field_access.const_field_info = field_access.const_field_info;
3179 a.Store(value_field_access, value);
3180 value = effect = a.Finish();
3181
3182 field_access.type = Type::Any();
3183 field_access.machine_type = MachineType::TaggedPointer();
3184 field_access.write_barrier_kind = kPointerWriteBarrier;
3185 } else {
3186 // We just store directly to the HeapNumber.
3187 FieldAccess const storage_access = {
3188 kTaggedBase,
3189 field_index.offset(),
3190 name.object(),
3191 OptionalMapRef(),
3192 Type::OtherInternal(),
3193 MachineType::TaggedPointer(),
3194 kPointerWriteBarrier,
3195 "BuildPropertyStore",
3196 access_info.GetConstFieldInfo(),
3197 access_mode == AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral};
3198 storage = effect =
3199 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(storage_access), storage,
3200 effect, control);
3201 FieldAccess value_field_access = AccessBuilder::ForHeapNumberValue();
3202 value_field_access.const_field_info = field_access.const_field_info;
3203 value_field_access.is_store_in_literal =
3204 field_access.is_store_in_literal;
3205 field_access = value_field_access;
3206 }
3207 break;
3208 }
3209 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned:
3210 case MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer:
3211 case MachineRepresentation::kTagged:
3212 if (field_representation == MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned) {
3213 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3214 simplified()->CheckSmi(FeedbackSource()), value, effect, control);
3215 field_access.write_barrier_kind = kNoWriteBarrier;
3216
3217 } else if (field_representation ==
3218 MachineRepresentation::kTaggedPointer) {
3219 OptionalMapRef field_map = access_info.field_map();
3220 if (field_map.has_value()) {
3221 // Emit a map check for the value.
3222 effect = graph()->NewNode(
3223 simplified()->CheckMaps(CheckMapsFlag::kNone,
3224 ZoneRefSet<Map>(*field_map)),
3225 value, effect, control);
3226 } else {
3227 // Ensure that {value} is a HeapObject.
3228 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckHeapObject(),
3229 value, effect, control);
3230 }
3231 field_access.write_barrier_kind = kPointerWriteBarrier;
3232
3233 } else {
3234 DCHECK(field_representation == MachineRepresentation::kTagged);
3235 }
3236 break;
3237 case MachineRepresentation::kNone:
3238 case MachineRepresentation::kBit:
3239 case MachineRepresentation::kCompressedPointer:
3240 case MachineRepresentation::kCompressed:
3241 case MachineRepresentation::kProtectedPointer:
3242 case MachineRepresentation::kIndirectPointer:
3243 case MachineRepresentation::kSandboxedPointer:
3244 case MachineRepresentation::kWord8:
3245 case MachineRepresentation::kWord16:
3246 case MachineRepresentation::kWord32:
3247 case MachineRepresentation::kWord64:
3248 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat16:
3249 case MachineRepresentation::kFloat32:
3250 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd128:
3251 case MachineRepresentation::kSimd256:
3252 case MachineRepresentation::kMapWord:
3253 UNREACHABLE();
3254 }
3255 // Check if we need to perform a transitioning store.
3256 OptionalMapRef transition_map = access_info.transition_map();
3257 if (transition_map.has_value()) {
3258 // Check if we need to grow the properties backing store
3259 // with this transitioning store.
3260 MapRef transition_map_ref = transition_map.value();
3261 MapRef original_map = transition_map_ref.GetBackPointer(broker()).AsMap();
3262 if (!field_index.is_inobject()) {
3263 // If slack tracking ends after this compilation started but before it's
3264 // finished, then we could {original_map} could be out-of-sync with
3265 // {transition_map_ref}. In particular, its UnusedPropertyFields could
3266 // be non-zero, which would lead us to not extend the property backing
3267 // store, while the underlying Map has actually zero
3268 // UnusedPropertyFields. Thus, we install a dependency on {orininal_map}
3269 // now, so that if such a situation happens, we'll throw away the code.
3270 dependencies()->DependOnNoSlackTrackingChange(original_map);
3271 }
3272 if (original_map.UnusedPropertyFields() == 0) {
3273 DCHECK(!field_index.is_inobject());
3274
3275 // Reallocate the properties {storage}.
3276 storage = effect = BuildExtendPropertiesBackingStore(
3277 original_map, storage, effect, control);
3278
3279 // Perform the actual store.
3280 effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(field_access),
3281 storage, value, effect, control);
3282
3283 // Atomically switch to the new properties below.
3284 field_access = AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectPropertiesOrHashKnownPointer();
3285 value = storage;
3286 storage = receiver;
3287 }
3288 effect = graph()->NewNode(
3289 common()->BeginRegion(RegionObservability::kObservable), effect);
3290 effect = graph()->NewNode(
3291 simplified()->StoreField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()), receiver,
3292 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(transition_map_ref, broker()), effect,
3293 control);
3294 effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(field_access), storage,
3295 value, effect, control);
3296 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->FinishRegion(),
3297 jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant(), effect);
3298 } else {
3299 // Regular non-transitioning field store.
3300 effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreField(field_access), storage,
3301 value, effect, control);
3302 }
3303 }
3304
3305 return ValueEffectControl(value, effect, control);
3306}
