3349
3350JSNativeContextSpecialization::ValueEffectControl
3351JSNativeContextSpecialization::BuildElementAccess(
3352 Node* receiver, Node* index, Node* value, Node* effect, Node* control,
3353 Node* context, ElementAccessInfo const& access_info,
3354 KeyedAccessMode const& keyed_mode) {
3355 // TODO(bmeurer): We currently specialize based on elements kind. We should
3356 // also be able to properly support strings and other JSObjects here.
3357 ElementsKind elements_kind = access_info.elements_kind();
3358 ZoneVector<MapRef> const& receiver_maps =
3359 access_info.lookup_start_object_maps();
3360
3361 if (IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind) ||
3362 IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
3363 return BuildElementAccessForTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArray(
3364 receiver, index, value, effect, control, context, elements_kind,
3365 keyed_mode);
3366 }
3367
3368 // Load the elements for the {receiver}.
3369 Node* elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3370 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSObjectElements()), receiver,
3371 effect, control);
3372
3373 // Don't try to store to a copy-on-write backing store (unless supported by
3374 // the store mode).
3375 if (IsAnyStore(keyed_mode.access_mode()) &&
3376 IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind) &&
3377 !StoreModeHandlesCOW(keyed_mode.store_mode())) {
3378 effect = graph()->NewNode(
3379 simplified()->CheckMaps(CheckMapsFlag::kNone,
3380 ZoneRefSet<Map>(broker()->fixed_array_map())),
3381 elements, effect, control);
3382 }
3383
3384 // Check if the {receiver} is a JSArray.
3385 bool receiver_is_jsarray = HasOnlyJSArrayMaps(broker(), receiver_maps);
3386
3387 // Load the length of the {receiver}.
3388 Node* length = effect =
3389 receiver_is_jsarray
3390 ? graph()->NewNode(
3391 simplified()->LoadField(
3392 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(elements_kind)),
3393 receiver, effect, control)
3394 : graph()->NewNode(
3395 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayLength()),
3396 elements, effect, control);
3397
3398 // Check if we might need to grow the {elements} backing store.
3399 if (keyed_mode.IsStore() && StoreModeCanGrow(keyed_mode.store_mode())) {
3400 // For growing stores we validate the {index} below.
3401 } else if (keyed_mode.IsLoad() &&
3402 LoadModeHandlesOOB(keyed_mode.load_mode()) &&
3403 CanTreatHoleAsUndefined(receiver_maps)) {
3404 // Check that the {index} is a valid array index, we do the actual
3405 // bounds check below and just skip the store below if it's out of
3406 // bounds for the {receiver}.
3407 index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3408 simplified()->CheckBounds(FeedbackSource(),
3409 CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero),
3410 index, jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(Smi::kMaxValue), effect, control);
3411 } else {
3412 // Check that the {index} is in the valid range for the {receiver}.
3413 index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3414 simplified()->CheckBounds(FeedbackSource(),
3415 CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero),
3416 index, length, effect, control);
3417 }
3418
3419 // Compute the element access.
3420 Type element_type = Type::NonInternal();
3421 MachineType element_machine_type = MachineType::AnyTagged();
3422 if (IsDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
3423 element_type = Type::Number();
3424 element_machine_type = MachineType::Float64();
3425 } else if (IsSmiElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
3426 element_type = Type::SignedSmall();
3427 element_machine_type = MachineType::TaggedSigned();
3428 }
3429 ElementAccess element_access = {kTaggedBase, OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(FixedArray),
3430 element_type, element_machine_type,
3431 kFullWriteBarrier};
3432
3433 // Access the actual element.
3434 if (keyed_mode.access_mode() == AccessMode::kLoad) {
3435 // Compute the real element access type, which includes the hole in case
3436 // of holey backing stores.
3437 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
3438 element_access.type =
3439 Type::Union(element_type, Type::Hole(), graph()->zone());
3440 }
3441 if (elements_kind == HOLEY_ELEMENTS ||
3442 elements_kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS) {
3443 element_access.machine_type = MachineType::AnyTagged();
3444 }
3445
3446 // Check if we can return undefined for out-of-bounds loads.
3447 if (LoadModeHandlesOOB(keyed_mode.load_mode()) &&
3448 CanTreatHoleAsUndefined(receiver_maps)) {
3449 Node* check =
3450 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index, length);
3451 Node* branch =
3452 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, control);
3453
3454 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
3455 Node* etrue = effect;
3456 Node* vtrue;
3457 {
3458 // Do a real bounds check against {length}. This is in order to
3459 // protect against a potential typer bug leading to the elimination of
3460 // the NumberLessThan above.
3461 if (v8_flags.turbo_typer_hardening) {
3462 index = etrue =
3463 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckBounds(
3464 FeedbackSource(),
3465 CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero |
3466 CheckBoundsFlag::kAbortOnOutOfBounds),
3467 index, length, etrue, if_true);
3468 }
3469
3470 // Perform the actual load
3471 vtrue = etrue =
3472 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadElement(element_access),
3473 elements, index, etrue, if_true);
3474
3475 // Handle loading from holey backing stores correctly by mapping
3476 // the hole to undefined.
3477 if (elements_kind == HOLEY_ELEMENTS ||
3478 elements_kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS) {
3479 // Turn the hole into undefined.
3480 vtrue = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined(),
3481 vtrue);
3482 } else if (elements_kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
3483 // Return the signaling NaN hole directly if all uses are
3484 // truncating.
3485 if (LoadModeHandlesHoles(keyed_mode.load_mode())) {
3486 vtrue = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ChangeFloat64HoleToTagged(),
3487 vtrue);
3488 } else {
3489 vtrue = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
3490 simplified()->CheckFloat64Hole(
3491 CheckFloat64HoleMode::kAllowReturnHole, FeedbackSource()),
3492 vtrue, etrue, if_true);
3493 }
3494 }
3495 }
3496
3497 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
3498 Node* efalse = effect;
3499 Node* vfalse;
3500 {
3501 // Materialize undefined for out-of-bounds loads.
3502 vfalse = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
3503 }
3504
3505 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
3506 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
3507 value = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
3508 vtrue, vfalse, control);
3509 } else {
3510 // Perform the actual load.
3511 value = effect =
3512 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadElement(element_access), elements,
3513 index, effect, control);
3514
3515 // Handle loading from holey backing stores correctly, by either mapping
3516 // the hole to undefined if possible, or deoptimizing otherwise.
3517 if (elements_kind == HOLEY_ELEMENTS ||
3518 elements_kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS) {
3519 // Check if we are allowed to turn the hole into undefined.
3520 if (CanTreatHoleAsUndefined(receiver_maps)) {
3521 // Turn the hole into undefined.
3522 value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ConvertTaggedHoleToUndefined(),
3523 value);
3524 } else {
3525 // Bailout if we see the hole.
3526 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckNotTaggedHole(),
3527 value, effect, control);
3528 }
3529 } else if (elements_kind == HOLEY_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS) {
3530 // Perform the hole check on the result.
3531 // Check if we are allowed to return the hole directly.
3532 if (CanTreatHoleAsUndefined(receiver_maps)) {
3533 if (LoadModeHandlesHoles(keyed_mode.load_mode())) {
3534 // Return the signaling NaN hole directly if all uses are
3535 // truncating.
3536 value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ChangeFloat64HoleToTagged(),
3537 value);
3538 } else {
3539 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3540 simplified()->CheckFloat64Hole(
3541 CheckFloat64HoleMode::kAllowReturnHole, FeedbackSource()),
3542 value, effect, control);
3543 }
3544 } else {
3545 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3546 simplified()->CheckFloat64Hole(
3547 CheckFloat64HoleMode::kNeverReturnHole, FeedbackSource()),
3548 value, effect, control);
3549 }
3550 }
3551 }
3552 } else if (keyed_mode.access_mode() == AccessMode::kHas) {
3553 // For packed arrays with NoElementsProctector valid, a bound check
3554 // is equivalent to HasProperty.
3555 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->SpeculativeNumberLessThan(
3556 NumberOperationHint::kSignedSmall),
3557 index, length, effect, control);
3558 if (IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
3559 // If the index is in bounds, do a load and hole check.
3560
3561 Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), value, control);
3562
3563 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
3564 Node* efalse = effect;
3565 Node* vfalse = jsgraph()->FalseConstant();
3566
3567 element_access.type =
3568 Type::Union(element_type, Type::Hole(), graph()->zone());
3569
3570 if (elements_kind == HOLEY_ELEMENTS ||
3571 elements_kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS) {
3572 element_access.machine_type = MachineType::AnyTagged();
3573 }
3574
3575 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
3576 Node* etrue = effect;
3577
3578 Node* checked = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
3579 simplified()->CheckBounds(
3580 FeedbackSource(), CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero),
3581 index, length, etrue, if_true);
3582
3583 Node* element = etrue =
3584 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadElement(element_access), elements,
3585 checked, etrue, if_true);
3586
3587 Node* vtrue;
3588 if (CanTreatHoleAsUndefined(receiver_maps)) {
3589 if (elements_kind == HOLEY_ELEMENTS ||
3590 elements_kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS) {
3591 // Check if we are allowed to turn the hole into undefined.
3592 // Turn the hole into undefined.
3593 vtrue = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ReferenceEqual(), element,
3594 jsgraph()->TheHoleConstant());
3595 } else {
3596 vtrue =
3597 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberIsFloat64Hole(), element);
3598 }
3599
3600 // has == !IsHole
3601 vtrue = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->BooleanNot(), vtrue);
3602 } else {
3603 if (elements_kind == HOLEY_ELEMENTS ||
3604 elements_kind == HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS) {
3605 // Bailout if we see the hole.
3606 etrue = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckNotTaggedHole(), element,
3607 etrue, if_true);
3608 } else {
3609 etrue = graph()->NewNode(
3610 simplified()->CheckFloat64Hole(
3611 CheckFloat64HoleMode::kNeverReturnHole, FeedbackSource()),
3612 element, etrue, if_true);
3613 }
3614
3615 vtrue = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
3616 }
3617
3618 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
3619 effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
3620 value = graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
3621 vtrue, vfalse, control);
3622 }
3623 } else {
3624 DCHECK(keyed_mode.access_mode() == AccessMode::kStore ||
3625 keyed_mode.access_mode() == AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral ||
3626 keyed_mode.access_mode() == AccessMode::kDefine);
3627
3628 if (IsSmiElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
3629 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3630 simplified()->CheckSmi(FeedbackSource()), value, effect, control);
3631 } else if (IsDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
3632 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3633 simplified()->CheckNumber(FeedbackSource()), value, effect, control);
3634 // Make sure we do not store signalling NaNs into double arrays.
3635 value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberSilenceNaN(), value);
3636 }
3637
3638 // Ensure that copy-on-write backing store is writable.
3639 if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind) &&
3640 keyed_mode.store_mode() == KeyedAccessStoreMode::kHandleCOW) {
3641 elements = effect =
3642 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->EnsureWritableFastElements(), receiver,
3643 elements, effect, control);
3644 } else if (StoreModeCanGrow(keyed_mode.store_mode())) {
3645 // Determine the length of the {elements} backing store.
3646 Node* elements_length = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3647 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArrayLength()),
3648 elements, effect, control);
3649
3650 // Validate the {index} depending on holeyness:
3651 //
3652 // For HOLEY_*_ELEMENTS the {index} must not exceed the {elements}
3653 // backing store capacity plus the maximum allowed gap, as otherwise
3654 // the (potential) backing store growth would normalize and thus
3655 // the elements kind of the {receiver} would change to slow mode.
3656 //
3657 // For JSArray PACKED_*_ELEMENTS the {index} must be within the range
3658 // [0,length+1[ to be valid. In case {index} equals {length},
3659 // the {receiver} will be extended, but kept packed.
3660 //
3661 // Non-JSArray PACKED_*_ELEMENTS always grow by adding holes because they
3662 // lack the magical length property, which requires a map transition.
3663 // So we can assume that this did not happen if we did not see this map.
3664 Node* limit =
3665 IsHoleyElementsKind(elements_kind)
3666 ? graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), elements_length,
3667 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JSObject::kMaxGap))
3668 : receiver_is_jsarray
3669 ? graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), length,
3670 jsgraph()->OneConstant())
3671 : elements_length;
3672 index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3673 simplified()->CheckBounds(
3674 FeedbackSource(), CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero),
3675 index, limit, effect, control);
3676
3677 // Grow {elements} backing store if necessary.
3678 GrowFastElementsMode mode =
3679 IsDoubleElementsKind(elements_kind)
3680 ? GrowFastElementsMode::kDoubleElements
3681 : GrowFastElementsMode::kSmiOrObjectElements;
3682 elements = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3683 simplified()->MaybeGrowFastElements(mode, FeedbackSource()), receiver,
3684 elements, index, elements_length, effect, control);
3685
3686 // If we didn't grow {elements}, it might still be COW, in which case we
3687 // copy it now.
3688 if (IsSmiOrObjectElementsKind(elements_kind) &&
3689 keyed_mode.store_mode() == KeyedAccessStoreMode::kGrowAndHandleCOW) {
3690 elements = effect =
3691 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->EnsureWritableFastElements(),
3692 receiver, elements, effect, control);
3693 }
3694
3695 // Also update the "length" property if {receiver} is a JSArray.
3696 if (receiver_is_jsarray) {
3697 Node* check =
3698 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index, length);
3699 Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(), check, control);
3700
3701 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
3702 Node* etrue = effect;
3703 {
3704 // We don't need to do anything, the {index} is within
3705 // the valid bounds for the JSArray {receiver}.
3706 }
3707
3708 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
3709 Node* efalse = effect;
3710 {
3711 // Update the JSArray::length field. Since this is observable,
3712 // there must be no other check after this.
3713 Node* new_length = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberAdd(), index,
3714 jsgraph()->OneConstant());
3715 efalse = graph()->NewNode(
3716 simplified()->StoreField(
3717 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayLength(elements_kind)),
3718 receiver, new_length, efalse, if_false);
3719 }
3720
3721 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
3722 effect =
3723 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
3724 }
3725 }
3726
3727 // Perform the actual element access.
3728 effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StoreElement(element_access),
3729 elements, index, value, effect, control);
3730 }
3731
3732 return ValueEffectControl(value, effect, control);
3733}
3734
3735JSNativeContextSpecialization::ValueEffectControl
3736JSNativeContextSpecialization::
3737 BuildElementAccessForTypedArrayOrRabGsabTypedArray(
3738 Node* receiver, Node* index, Node* value, Node* effect, Node* control,
3739 Node* context, ElementsKind elements_kind,
3740 KeyedAccessMode const& keyed_mode) {
3741 DCHECK(IsTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind) ||
3742 IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind));
3743 // AccessMode::kDefine is not handled here. Optimization should be skipped by
3744 // caller.
3745 DCHECK(keyed_mode.access_mode() != AccessMode::kDefine);
3746
3747 Node* buffer_or_receiver = receiver;
3748 Node* length;
3749 Node* base_pointer;
3750 Node* external_pointer;
3751
3752 // Check if we can constant-fold information about the {receiver} (e.g.
3753 // for asm.js-like code patterns).
3754 OptionalJSTypedArrayRef typed_array =
3755 GetTypedArrayConstant(broker(), receiver);
3756 if (typed_array.has_value() &&
3757 // TODO(v8:11111): Add support for rab/gsab here.
3758 !IsRabGsabTypedArrayElementsKind(elements_kind)) {
3759 if (typed_array->map(broker()).elements_kind() != elements_kind) {
3760 // This case should never be reachable at runtime.
3761 JSGraphAssembler assembler(broker(), jsgraph_, zone(),
3762 BranchSemantics::kJS,
3763 [this](Node* n) { this->Revisit(n); });
3764 assembler.InitializeEffectControl(effect, control);
3765 assembler.Unreachable();
3766 ReleaseEffectAndControlFromAssembler(&assembler);
3767 Node* dead = jsgraph_->Dead();
3768 return ValueEffectControl{dead, dead, dead};
3769 } else {
3770 length =
3771 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(static_cast<double>(typed_array->length()));
3772
3773 DCHECK(!typed_array->is_on_heap());
3774 // Load the (known) data pointer for the {receiver} and set
3775 // {base_pointer} and {external_pointer} to the values that will allow
3776 // to generate typed element accesses using the known data pointer. The
3777 // data pointer might be invalid if the {buffer} was detached, so we
3778 // need to make sure that any access is properly guarded.
3779 base_pointer = jsgraph()->ZeroConstant();
3780 external_pointer = jsgraph()->PointerConstant(typed_array->data_ptr());
3781 }
3782 } else {
3783 // Load the {receiver}s length.
3784 JSGraphAssembler assembler(broker(), jsgraph_, zone(), BranchSemantics::kJS,
3785 [this](Node* n) { this->Revisit(n); });
3786 assembler.InitializeEffectControl(effect, control);
3787 length = assembler.TypedArrayLength(
3788 TNode<JSTypedArray>::UncheckedCast(receiver), {elements_kind},
3789 TNode<Context>::UncheckedCast(context));
3790 std::tie(effect, control) =
3791 ReleaseEffectAndControlFromAssembler(&assembler);
3792
3793 // Load the base pointer for the {receiver}. This will always be Smi
3794 // zero unless we allow on-heap TypedArrays, which is only the case
3795 // for Chrome. Node and Electron both set this limit to 0. Setting
3796 // the base to Smi zero here allows the EffectControlLinearizer to
3797 // optimize away the tricky part of the access later.
3798 if (JSTypedArray::kMaxSizeInHeap == 0) {
3799 base_pointer = jsgraph()->ZeroConstant();
3800 } else {
3801 base_pointer = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3802 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayBasePointer()),
3803 receiver, effect, control);
3804 }
3805
3806 // Load the external pointer for the {receiver}.
3807 external_pointer = effect =
3808 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(
3809 AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayExternalPointer()),
3810 receiver, effect, control);
3811 }
3812
3813 // See if we can skip the detaching check.
3814 if (!dependencies()->DependOnArrayBufferDetachingProtector()) {
3815 // Load the buffer for the {receiver}.
3816 Node* buffer =
3817 typed_array.has_value()
3818 ? jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(typed_array->buffer(broker()), broker())
3819 : (effect = graph()->NewNode(
3820 simplified()->LoadField(
3821 AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferViewBuffer()),
3822 receiver, effect, control));
3823
3824 // Deopt if the {buffer} was detached.
3825 // Note: A detached buffer leads to megamorphic feedback.
3826 Node* buffer_bit_field = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3827 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForJSArrayBufferBitField()),
3828 buffer, effect, control);
3829 Node* check = graph()->NewNode(
3830 simplified()->NumberEqual(),
3831 graph()->NewNode(
3832 simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), buffer_bit_field,
3833 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(JSArrayBuffer::WasDetachedBit::kMask)),
3834 jsgraph()->ZeroConstant());
3835 effect = graph()->NewNode(
3836 simplified()->CheckIf(DeoptimizeReason::kArrayBufferWasDetached), check,
3837 effect, control);
3838
3839 // Retain the {buffer} instead of {receiver} to reduce live ranges.
3840 buffer_or_receiver = buffer;
3841 }
3842
3843 enum Situation { kBoundsCheckDone, kHandleOOB_SmiAndRangeCheckComputed };
3844 Situation situation;
3845 TNode<BoolT> check;
3846 if ((keyed_mode.IsLoad() && LoadModeHandlesOOB(keyed_mode.load_mode())) ||
3847 (keyed_mode.IsStore() &&
3848 StoreModeIgnoresTypeArrayOOB(keyed_mode.store_mode()))) {
3849 // Only check that the {index} is in SignedSmall range. We do the actual
3850 // bounds check below and just skip the property access if it's out of
3851 // bounds for the {receiver}.
3852 index = effect = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->CheckSmi(FeedbackSource()),
3853 index, effect, control);
3854 TNode<Boolean> compare_length = TNode<Boolean>::UncheckedCast(
3855 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index, length));
3856
3857 JSGraphAssembler assembler(broker(), jsgraph_, zone(), BranchSemantics::kJS,
3858 [this](Node* n) { this->Revisit(n); });
3859 assembler.InitializeEffectControl(effect, control);
3860 TNode<BoolT> check_less_than_length =
3861 assembler.EnterMachineGraph<BoolT>(compare_length, UseInfo::Bool());
3862 TNode<Int32T> index_int32 = assembler.EnterMachineGraph<Int32T>(
3863 TNode<Smi>::UncheckedCast(index), UseInfo::TruncatingWord32());
3864 TNode<BoolT> check_non_negative =
3865 assembler.Int32LessThanOrEqual(assembler.Int32Constant(0), index_int32);
3866 check = TNode<BoolT>::UncheckedCast(
3867 assembler.Word32And(check_less_than_length, check_non_negative));
3868 std::tie(effect, control) =
3869 ReleaseEffectAndControlFromAssembler(&assembler);
3870
3871 situation = kHandleOOB_SmiAndRangeCheckComputed;
3872 } else {
3873 // Check that the {index} is in the valid range for the {receiver}.
3874 index = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3875 simplified()->CheckBounds(FeedbackSource(),
3876 CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero),
3877 index, length, effect, control);
3878 situation = kBoundsCheckDone;
3879 }
3880
3881 // Access the actual element.
3882 ExternalArrayType external_array_type =
3883 GetArrayTypeFromElementsKind(elements_kind);
3884 DCHECK_NE(external_array_type, ExternalArrayType::kExternalFloat16Array);
3885 switch (keyed_mode.access_mode()) {
3886 case AccessMode::kLoad: {
3887 // Check if we can return undefined for out-of-bounds loads.
3888 if (situation == kHandleOOB_SmiAndRangeCheckComputed) {
3889 DCHECK_NE(check, nullptr);
3890 Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(
3891 common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue, BranchSemantics::kMachine),
3892 check, control);
3893
3894 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
3895 Node* etrue = effect;
3896 Node* vtrue;
3897 {
3898 // Do a real bounds check against {length}. This is in order to
3899 // protect against a potential typer bug leading to the elimination
3900 // of the NumberLessThan above.
3901 if (v8_flags.turbo_typer_hardening) {
3902 index = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
3903 simplified()->CheckBounds(
3904 FeedbackSource(),
3905 CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero |
3906 CheckBoundsFlag::kAbortOnOutOfBounds),
3907 index, length, etrue, if_true);
3908 }
3909
3910 // Perform the actual load
3911 vtrue = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
3912 simplified()->LoadTypedElement(external_array_type),
3913 buffer_or_receiver, base_pointer, external_pointer, index, etrue,
3914 if_true);
3915 }
3916
3917 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
3918 Node* efalse = effect;
3919 Node* vfalse;
3920 {
3921 // Materialize undefined for out-of-bounds loads.
3922 vfalse = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
3923 }
3924
3925 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
3926 effect =
3927 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
3928 value =
3929 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
3930 vtrue, vfalse, control);
3931 } else {
3932 // Perform the actual load.
3933 DCHECK_EQ(kBoundsCheckDone, situation);
3934 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3935 simplified()->LoadTypedElement(external_array_type),
3936 buffer_or_receiver, base_pointer, external_pointer, index, effect,
3937 control);
3938 }
3939 break;
3940 }
3941 case AccessMode::kStoreInLiteral:
3942 case AccessMode::kDefine:
3943 UNREACHABLE();
3944 case AccessMode::kStore: {
3945 if (external_array_type == kExternalBigInt64Array ||
3946 external_array_type == kExternalBigUint64Array) {
3947 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3948 simplified()->SpeculativeToBigInt(BigIntOperationHint::kBigInt,
3949 FeedbackSource()),
3950 value, effect, control);
3951 } else {
3952 // Ensure that the {value} is actually a Number or an Oddball,
3953 // and truncate it to a Number appropriately.
3954 // TODO(panq): Eliminate the deopt loop introduced by the speculation.
3955 value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
3956 simplified()->SpeculativeToNumber(
3957 NumberOperationHint::kNumberOrOddball, FeedbackSource()),
3958 value, effect, control);
3959 }
3960
3961 // Introduce the appropriate truncation for {value}. Currently we
3962 // only need to do this for ClamedUint8Array {receiver}s, as the
3963 // other truncations are implicit in the StoreTypedElement, but we
3964 // might want to change that at some point.
3965 if (external_array_type == kExternalUint8ClampedArray) {
3966 value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberToUint8Clamped(), value);
3967 }
3968
3969 if (situation == kHandleOOB_SmiAndRangeCheckComputed) {
3970 // We have to detect OOB stores and handle them without deopt (by
3971 // simply not performing them).
3972 DCHECK_NE(check, nullptr);
3973 Node* branch = graph()->NewNode(
3974 common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue, BranchSemantics::kMachine),
3975 check, control);
3976
3977 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
3978 Node* etrue = effect;
3979 {
3980 // Do a real bounds check against {length}. This is in order to
3981 // protect against a potential typer bug leading to the elimination
3982 // of the NumberLessThan above.
3983 if (v8_flags.turbo_typer_hardening) {
3984 index = etrue = graph()->NewNode(
3985 simplified()->CheckBounds(
3986 FeedbackSource(),
3987 CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero |
3988 CheckBoundsFlag::kAbortOnOutOfBounds),
3989 index, length, etrue, if_true);
3990 }
3991
3992 // Perform the actual store.
3993 etrue = graph()->NewNode(
3994 simplified()->StoreTypedElement(external_array_type),
3995 buffer_or_receiver, base_pointer, external_pointer, index, value,
3996 etrue, if_true);
3997 }
3998
3999 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
4000 Node* efalse = effect;
4001 {
4002 // Just ignore the out-of-bounds write.
4003 }
4004
4005 control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
4006 effect =
4007 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, efalse, control);
4008 } else {
4009 // Perform the actual store
4010 DCHECK_EQ(kBoundsCheckDone, situation);
4011 effect = graph()->NewNode(
4012 simplified()->StoreTypedElement(external_array_type),
4013 buffer_or_receiver, base_pointer, external_pointer, index, value,
4014 effect, control);
4015 }
4016 break;
4017 }
4018 case AccessMode::kHas:
4019 if (situation == kHandleOOB_SmiAndRangeCheckComputed) {
4020 DCHECK_NE(check, nullptr);
4021 JSGraphAssembler assembler(broker(), jsgraph_, zone(),
4022 BranchSemantics::kJS,
4023 [this](Node* n) { this->Revisit(n); });
4024 assembler.InitializeEffectControl(effect, control);
4025 value = assembler.MachineSelectIf<Boolean>(check)
4026 .Then([&]() { return assembler.TrueConstant(); })
4027 .Else([&]() { return assembler.FalseConstant(); })
4028 .ExpectTrue()
4029 .Value();
4030 std::tie(effect, control) =
4031 ReleaseEffectAndControlFromAssembler(&assembler);
4032 } else {
4033 DCHECK_EQ(kBoundsCheckDone, situation);
4034 // For has-property on a typed array, all we need is a bounds check.
4035 value = jsgraph()->TrueConstant();
4036 }
4037 break;
4038 }
4039
4040 return ValueEffectControl(value, effect, control);
4041}

4043Node* JSNativeContextSpecialization::BuildIndexedStringLoad(
4044 Node* receiver, Node* index, Node* length, Node** effect, Node** control,
4045 KeyedAccessLoadMode load_mode) {
4046 if (LoadModeHandlesOOB(load_mode) &&
4047 dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector()) {
4048 // Ensure that the {index} is a valid String length.
4049 index = *effect = graph()->NewNode(
4050 simplified()->CheckBounds(FeedbackSource(),
4051 CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero),
4052 index, jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(String::kMaxLength), *effect,
4053 *control);
4054
4055 // Load the single character string from {receiver} or yield
4056 // undefined if the {index} is not within the valid bounds.
4057 Node* check =
4058 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberLessThan(), index, length);
4059 Node* branch =
4060 graph()->NewNode(common()->Branch(BranchHint::kTrue), check, *control);
4061
4062 Node* if_true = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfTrue(), branch);
4063 // Do a real bounds check against {length}. This is in order to protect
4064 // against a potential typer bug leading to the elimination of the
4065 // NumberLessThan above.
4066 Node* etrue = *effect;
4067 if (v8_flags.turbo_typer_hardening) {
4068 etrue = index = graph()->NewNode(
4069 simplified()->CheckBounds(
4070 FeedbackSource(), CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero |
4071 CheckBoundsFlag::kAbortOnOutOfBounds),
4072 index, length, etrue, if_true);
4073 }
4074 Node* vtrue = etrue = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringCharCodeAt(),
4075 receiver, index, etrue, if_true);
4076 vtrue = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringFromSingleCharCode(), vtrue);
4077
4078 Node* if_false = graph()->NewNode(common()->IfFalse(), branch);
4079 Node* vfalse = jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant();
4080
4081 *control = graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), if_true, if_false);
4082 *effect =
4083 graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), etrue, *effect, *control);
4084 return graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, 2),
4085 vtrue, vfalse, *control);
4086 } else {
4087 // Ensure that {index} is less than {receiver} length.
4088 index = *effect = graph()->NewNode(
4089 simplified()->CheckBounds(FeedbackSource(),
4090 CheckBoundsFlag::kConvertStringAndMinusZero),
4091 index, length, *effect, *control);
4092
4093 // Return the character from the {receiver} as single character string.
4094 Node* value = *effect = graph()->NewNode(
4095 simplified()->StringCharCodeAt(), receiver, index, *effect, *control);
4096 value = graph()->NewNode(simplified()->StringFromSingleCharCode(), value);
4097 return value;
4098 }

4100
4101Node* JSNativeContextSpecialization::BuildExtendPropertiesBackingStore(
4102 MapRef map, Node* properties, Node* effect, Node* control) {
4103 // TODO(bmeurer/jkummerow): Property deletions can undo map transitions
4104 // while keeping the backing store around, meaning that even though the
4105 // map might believe that objects have no unused property fields, there
4106 // might actually be some. It would be nice to not create a new backing
4107 // store in that case (i.e. when properties->length() >= new_length).
4108 // However, introducing branches and Phi nodes here would make it more
4109 // difficult for escape analysis to get rid of the backing stores used
4110 // for intermediate states of chains of property additions. That makes
4111 // it unclear what the best approach is here.
4112 DCHECK_EQ(map.UnusedPropertyFields(), 0);
4113 int length = map.NextFreePropertyIndex() - map.GetInObjectProperties();
4114 // Under normal circumstances, NextFreePropertyIndex() will always be larger
4115 // than GetInObjectProperties(). However, an attacker able to corrupt heap
4116 // memory can break this invariant, in which case we'll get confused here,
4117 // potentially causing a sandbox violation. This CHECK defends against that.
4118 SBXCHECK_GE(length, 0);
4119 int new_length = length + JSObject::kFieldsAdded;
4120 // Collect the field values from the {properties}.
4121 ZoneVector<Node*> values(zone());
4122 values.reserve(new_length);
4123 for (int i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
4124 Node* value = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4125 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArraySlot(i)),
4126 properties, effect, control);
4127 values.push_back(value);
4128 }
4129 // Initialize the new fields to undefined.
4130 for (int i = 0; i < JSObject::kFieldsAdded; ++i) {
4131 values.push_back(jsgraph()->UndefinedConstant());
4132 }
4133
4134 // Compute new length and hash.
4135 Node* hash;
4136 if (length == 0) {
4137 hash = graph()->NewNode(
4138 common()->Select(MachineRepresentation::kTaggedSigned),
4139 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->ObjectIsSmi(), properties), properties,
4140 jsgraph()->SmiConstant(PropertyArray::kNoHashSentinel));
4141 hash = effect = graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::SignedSmall()),
4142 hash, effect, control);
4143 hash = graph()->NewNode(
4144 simplified()->NumberShiftLeft(), hash,
4145 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(PropertyArray::HashField::kShift));
4146 } else {
4147 hash = effect = graph()->NewNode(
4148 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForPropertyArrayLengthAndHash()),
4149 properties, effect, control);
4150 hash = graph()->NewNode(
4151 simplified()->NumberBitwiseAnd(), hash,
4152 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(PropertyArray::HashField::kMask));
4153 }
4154 Node* new_length_and_hash =
4155 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->NumberBitwiseOr(),
4156 jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(new_length), hash);
4157 // TDOO(jarin): Fix the typer to infer tighter bound for NumberBitwiseOr.
4158 new_length_and_hash = effect =
4159 graph()->NewNode(common()->TypeGuard(Type::SignedSmall()),
4160 new_length_and_hash, effect, control);
4161
4162 // Allocate and initialize the new properties.
4163 AllocationBuilder a(jsgraph(), broker(), effect, control);
4164 a.Allocate(PropertyArray::SizeFor(new_length), AllocationType::kYoung,
4165 Type::OtherInternal());
4166 a.Store(AccessBuilder::ForMap(), jsgraph()->PropertyArrayMapConstant());
4167 a.Store(AccessBuilder::ForPropertyArrayLengthAndHash(), new_length_and_hash);
4168 for (int i = 0; i < new_length; ++i) {
4169 a.Store(AccessBuilder::ForFixedArraySlot(i), values[i]);
4170 }
4171 return a.Finish();
4172}
4173
4174Node* JSNativeContextSpecialization::BuildCheckEqualsName(NameRef name,
4175 Node* value,
4176 Node* effect,
4177 Node* control) {
4178 DCHECK(name.IsUniqueName());
4179 Operator const* const op =
4180 name.IsSymbol() ? simplified()->CheckEqualsSymbol()
4181 : simplified()->CheckEqualsInternalizedString();
4182 return graph()->NewNode(op, jsgraph()->ConstantNoHole(name, broker()), value,
4183 effect, control);
4184}
4185
4186bool JSNativeContextSpecialization::CanTreatHoleAsUndefined(
4187 ZoneVector<MapRef> const& receiver_maps) {
4188 // Check if all {receiver_maps} have one of the initial Array.prototype
4189 // or Object.prototype objects as their prototype (in any of the current
4190 // native contexts, as the global Array protector works isolate-wide).
4191 for (MapRef receiver_map : receiver_maps) {
4192 ObjectRef receiver_prototype = receiver_map.prototype(broker());
4193 if (!receiver_prototype.IsJSObject() ||
4194 !broker()->IsArrayOrObjectPrototype(receiver_prototype.AsJSObject())) {
4195 return false;
4196 }
4197 }
4198
4199 // Check if the array prototype chain is intact.
4200 return dependencies()->DependOnNoElementsProtector();
4201}
4202
4203bool JSNativeContextSpecialization::InferMaps(Node* object, Effect effect,
4204 ZoneVector<MapRef>* maps) const {
4205 ZoneRefSet<Map> map_set;
4206 NodeProperties::InferMapsResult result =
4207 NodeProperties::InferMapsUnsafe(broker(), object, effect, &map_set);
4208 if (result == NodeProperties::kReliableMaps) {
4209 for (MapRef map : map_set) {
4210 maps->push_back(map);
4211 }
4212 return true;
4213 } else if (result == NodeProperties::kUnreliableMaps) {
4214 // For untrusted maps, we can still use the information
4215 // if the maps are stable.
4216 for (MapRef map : map_set) {
4217 if (!map.is_stable()) return false;
4218 }
4219 for (MapRef map : map_set) {
4220 maps->push_back(map);
4221 }
4222 return true;
4223 }
4224 return false;
4225}
4226
4227OptionalMapRef JSNativeContextSpecialization::InferRootMap(Node* object) const {
4228 HeapObjectMatcher m(object);
4229 if (m.HasResolvedValue()) {
4230 MapRef map = m.Ref(broker()).map(broker());
4231 return map.FindRootMap(broker());
4232 } else if (m.IsJSCreate()) {
4233 OptionalMapRef initial_map =
4234 NodeProperties::GetJSCreateMap(broker(), object);
4235 if (initial_map.has_value()) {
4236 DCHECK(initial_map->equals(initial_map->FindRootMap(broker())));
4237 return *initial_map;
4238 }
4239 }
4240 return std::nullopt;
4241}

4243Node* JSNativeContextSpecialization::BuildLoadPrototypeFromObject(

4245 Node* map = effect =
4246 graph()->NewNode(simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMap()), object,
4247 effect, control);
4248 return graph()->NewNode(
4249 simplified()->LoadField(AccessBuilder::ForMapPrototype()), map, effect,
4250 control);

4253std::pair<Node*, Node*>
4254JSNativeContextSpecialization::ReleaseEffectAndControlFromAssembler(
4255 JSGraphAssembler* gasm) {
4256 auto catch_scope = gasm->catch_scope();
4257 DCHECK(catch_scope->is_outermost());
4258
4259 if (catch_scope->has_handler() &&
4260 catch_scope->has_exceptional_control_flow()) {
4261 TNode<Object> handler_exception;
4262 Effect handler_effect{nullptr};
4263 Control handler_control{nullptr};
4264 gasm->catch_scope()->MergeExceptionalPaths(
4265 &handler_exception, &handler_effect, &handler_control);
4266
4267 ReplaceWithValue(gasm->outermost_handler(), handler_exception,
4268 handler_effect, handler_control);
4269 }
4270
4271 return {gasm->effect(), gasm->control()};
4272}
